CASING.Name: CASING_NAME
CASING.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
CASING.Description_Text:
A lightweight metal product, heavily used in the manufacture of <TECHNOLOGY>starship parts<> and <TECHNOLOGY>deployable technology<>. A mainstay of the construction industries of all known primary species.

Crafted from <EARTH>Ferrite Dust<>.

NANOTUBES.Name: NANOTUBES_NAME
NANOTUBES.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
NANOTUBES.Description_Text:
Metres and metres of high capacity <FUEL>carbon nanotubes<>.

Their high tensile strength and mild conductivity make these a key component in many <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

CARBON_SEAL.Name: CARBON_SEAL_NAME
CARBON_SEAL.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
CARBON_SEAL.Description_Text:
A high-performance <FUEL>carbon seal<>, able to withstand both the harsh interstellar environment and the rigours of intensive, high-energy industrial use.

User is advised to regularly check seal integrity after installation.

MICROCHIP.Name: MICROCHIP_NAME
MICROCHIP.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
MICROCHIP.Description_Text:
A compact, <TECHNOLOGY>low-heat microchip<>. Assembled from processed <STELLAR>Chromatic Metal<>, created from one of several specialised terrain metals.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

HYDRALIC.Name: UI_HYDRALIC_NAME
HYDRALIC.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
HYDRALIC.Description_Text:
Specialist <TECHNOLOGY>wiring and control threads<>, this flexible material allows the transmission of power and signals, as well as offering direct manipulation of remote components.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

COMPUTER.Name: UI_COMPUTER_NAME
COMPUTER.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
COMPUTER.Description_Text:
An extremely fast <TECHNOLOGY>advanced processing unit<>. Allows real-time solving of otherwise impossible calculations. However, protection against decoherence is not guaranteed.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

MAGNET.Name: UI_MAGNET_NAME
MAGNET.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
MAGNET.Description_Text:
An electromagnetic <TECHNOLOGY>frequency oscillator<>, able to function in a wide-range of conditions thanks to both ferrous and non-ferrous magnetic properties.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

MIRROR.Name: UI_MIRROR_NAME
MIRROR.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
MIRROR.Description_Text:
A specialist optical component. Employing an impossibly polished surface, this mirror is able to selectively filter different wavelengths of light, changing its reflective pattern based on nearby magnetic fields.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

BIO.Name: UI_BIO_NAME
BIO.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
BIO.Description_Text:
A specialist <TECHNOLOGY>biological catalysation device<>.

This unit takes advantage of naturally occurring enzymes in order to facilitate increased energy yields and faster processing in a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

TECH_COMP.Name: UI_TECHMOD_NAME
TECH_COMP.Subtitle: UI_TECHMOD_SUB
TECH_COMP.Description_Text:
A prefabricated circuit board, designed for flexible use in a large range of <TECHNOLOGY>technology components<>.

The module features an integrated nanite processor, allowing it to be quickly configured for a wide variety of uses.

REPAIRKIT.Name: UI_REPAIR_KIT_NAME
REPAIRKIT.Subtitle: UI_REPAIR_KIT_SUB
REPAIRKIT.Description_Text:
A highly useful piece of <STELLAR>survival technology<>, the Repair Kit allows damaged equipment to be quickly and efficiently restored to working order.

While repairing a piece of techology, the Repair Kit can be applied to any damaged subcomponent in place of the usual requirements.

PRODFUEL2.Name: FUELGEL3_NAME
PRODFUEL2.Subtitle: FUELGEL_SUB
PRODFUEL2.Description_Text:
Emergency <FUEL>life support fuel<>.

Synthesised from <TECHNOLOGY>rocket fuel crystals<> and <FUEL>carbon<>, this gel offers a temporary boost to life support systems. Long-term impact on user's lungs is currently unknown.

POWERCELL.Name: POWERCELL_NAME
POWERCELL.Subtitle: POWERPROD_SUB
POWERCELL.Description_Text:
Convenient and optimised power storage unit. Used in a wide variety of <COMMODITY>defensive<> and <COMMODITY>hazard protection<> systems.
 
Constructed by fusing <EARTH>Ferrite Dust<> with underground <TECHNOLOGY>Cobalt<>. Frequently found ready-made in cylindrical metal containers.

SHIPCHARGE.Name: UI_SHIPCHARGE_NAME
SHIPCHARGE.Subtitle: POWERPROD_SUB
SHIPCHARGE.Description_Text:
A power storage unit optimised for use in <COMMODITY>starship defensive systems<>.
 
<SPECIAL>Tritium<>-fuelled capacitors provide quick-release charge for the <TECHNOLOGY>Deflector Shield<>, but would overload smaller-scale equipment.

JELLY.Name: FUEL_JELLY_NAME
JELLY.Subtitle: FUELGEL_SUB
JELLY.Description_Text:
A faintly-glowing jelly. Its gentle light and soft wobble belie the fact that this sticky gel is both highly toxic and highly flammable. Skin contact is to be avoided at all costs.

Synthesised from <TECHNOLOGY>Di-hydrogen<>.

LAUNCHFUEL.Name: LAUNCHFUEL_NAME
LAUNCHFUEL.Subtitle: LAUNCHFUEL_SUB
LAUNCHFUEL.Description_Text:
Highly reactive solid-state fuel, required to fuel <TECHNOLOGY>Starship Launch Thrusters<>.

Created from crystallised <TECHNOLOGY>Di-hydrogen<>, found in blue deposits on all worlds.

SUBFUEL.Name: UI_SUBFUEL_NAME
SUBFUEL.Subtitle: UI_SUBFUEL_SUB
SUBFUEL.Description_Text:
A high thermal energy fuel, contained within a standardised fuel cell. Used to fuel the <TECHNOLOGY>Humboldt Drive<> that powers the Nautilon submarine.

Created with a mix of organic compounds (<FUEL>Carbon<> and <TRADEABLE>cyto-phosphates<>) and localised mineral <TRADEABLE>salts<>.

GRENFUEL1.Name: GRENFUEL1_NAME
GRENFUEL1.Subtitle: GRENFUEL1_SUBTITLE
GRENFUEL1.Description_Text:
Densely-packed fuel capsule for use in the <TECHNOLOGY>Plasma Launcher<>.
 
Contained highly-pressurised electro-thermal energy for use in land disruption grenade technology.

AMMO.Name: AMMO_PROD_NAME
AMMO.Subtitle: AMMO_PROD_SUB
AMMO.Description_Text:
Advanced munition fragments, constructed to fit Universal Multi-Tool Standard 07/FF1.

Easily inserted into the <TECHNOLOGY>Boltcaster<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Pulse Spitter<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Scatter Blaster<> via the Multi-Tool clip reloading system.

AM_HOUSING.Name: AM_HOUSING_NAME
AM_HOUSING.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
AM_HOUSING.Description_Text:
Secure antimatter containment device, required before <FUEL>Antimatter<> can be safely secured as <FUEL>Warp Cells<>.

Rebound <FUEL>Oxygen<> forms a protective gas pocket, preventing the antimatter from reacting with the surrounding casing.

ANTIMATTER.Name: COMMODITY6_NAME
ANTIMATTER.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
ANTIMATTER.Description_Text:
Contained negative matter and baryogenesis antiparticles.
 
The vast energy potential of antimatter makes it highly valuable. 95% of existing antimatter consumption is in the powering of <TECHNOLOGY>starship hyperdrives<>.

<FUEL>WARNING<>: uncontained usage is not recommended.

HYPERFUEL1.Name: HYPERFUEL1_NAME
HYPERFUEL1.Subtitle: HYPERFUEL1_SUBTITLE
HYPERFUEL1.Description_Text:
This <FUEL>antimatter-based fuel<> is one of the few power sources capable of meeting the incredible energy requirements of a <TECHNOLOGY>starship hyperdrive<>.

Secured within a robust housing, the cell is guaranteed paradox-free during FTL travel.

HYPERFUEL2.Name: HYPERFUEL2_NAME
HYPERFUEL2.Subtitle: HYPERFUEL2_SUBTITLE
HYPERFUEL2.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>high-capacity<> <FUEL>antimatter-based fuel<>, this cell harnesses an internal black hole generator to power <TECHNOLOGY>starship hyperdrives<> across multiple warp jumps.

Cell walls are specially designed to reflect any reality paradoxes back towards the heart of the unit, where they generate additional power.

SENTINEL_LOOT.Name: UI_SENTINEL_LOOT_NAME
SENTINEL_LOOT.Subtitle: UI_SENTINEL_LOOT_SUB
SENTINEL_LOOT.Description_Text: A sinister shard of purple glass<>, salvaged from the destroyed remains of Sentinel machinery. Its walls are thin, and it may be broken down to access valuable Sentinel components. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and shatter with FE_ALT1<>.

QUAD_PROD.Name: UI_QUAD_PROD_NAME
QUAD_PROD.Subtitle: SUB_DEADDRONE_SUBTITLE
QUAD_PROD.Description_Text: A highly sprung motor arm salvaged from inside of a Sentinel patrol unit. It occasionally twitches, as if experiencing the echo of combat.

SPIDER_PROD.Name: UI_SPIDER_PROD_NAME
SPIDER_PROD.Subtitle: UI_SPIDER_PROD_SUB
SPIDER_PROD.Description_Text:
The functional core of a Sentinel quadruped unit, but warped beyond all recognition. The entire machine is infested with a crystalline material that pulses wildy upon inspection.

A close analysis reveals the machinery itself appears to have been reconfigured, stretching and warping into a whole new form, writhing in the presence of these radiant shards of glass.

MECH_PROD.Name: UI_MECH_PROD_NAME
MECH_PROD.Subtitle: SUB_DEADDRONE_SUBTITLE
MECH_PROD.Description_Text:
This complex mechanical unit was once the central combustion chamber at the heart of a <SPECIAL>Sentinel Hardframe<> unit.

Though now cool to the touch, it still glows with a sinister red heat...

WALKER_PROD.Name: UI_WALKER_PROD_NAME
WALKER_PROD.Subtitle: SUB_DEADDRONE_SUBTITLE
WALKER_PROD.Description_Text:
Shifting nanite clusters sewn together with a pugneum filament, this circuit is painfully hot to the touch.

A sinister purple light leaks from deep within its wiring, changing in intensity as it watches its holder.

QUEEN_PROD.Name: UI_QUEEN_PROD_NAME
QUEEN_PROD.Subtitle: UI_QUEEN_PROD_SUB
QUEEN_PROD.Description_Text:
The brain stem of a <TRADEABLE>brood mother<>, pulled from its malignant corpse.

This is a valuable trophy, signifying victory in the quest to purge the infestations of the vile brood. Turn it over to an envoy of the <TECHNOLOGY>Mercenaries Guild<> to mark your triumph.

PIRATE_PROD.Name: UI_PIRATE_PROD_NAME
PIRATE_PROD.Subtitle: UI_PIRATE_PROD_SUB
PIRATE_PROD.Description_Text:
A unique ID <TECHNOLOGY>transponder<>, ripped from the internal signal array of an <STELLAR>outlaw starship<>.

Possesion of such a device implies the destruction of the vessel in question. Turn it over to an envoy of the <TECHNOLOGY>Mercenaries Guild<> to collect any associated bounties.

DEEPSEA_PROD.Name: UI_DEEPSEA_PROD_NAME
DEEPSEA_PROD.Subtitle: UI_DEEPSEA_PROD_SUB
DEEPSEA_PROD.Description_Text:
A etheral shard, this translucent plane is both mineral and alive, both of the water and of another realm.

Of high value to collectors across the universe.

SHIPBRAIN.Name: UI_SHIP_BRAIN_NAME
SHIPBRAIN.Subtitle: UI_SHIP_BRAIN_SUB
SHIPBRAIN.Description_Text:
The central processing unit of a Sentinel interceptor ship. The circuitry writhes microscopically, constantly rearranging itself as it scans for anomalies.

A vital component for any entity wishing to construct their own <TECHNOLOGY>Pilot Interface<> for a Sentinel Interceptor.

Status: <FUEL>VOLATILE<>

SENTFREI_PROD.Name: UI_SENTFREI_PROD_NAME
SENTFREI_PROD.Subtitle: UI_SENTFREI_PROD_SUB
SENTFREI_PROD.Description_Text: A single splinter of the colossal mainframe at the heart of a Sentinel capital ship. It blinks, its solitary living eye trained upon the one piece of data it retains - the last known location of one of its fleet of Interceptors<>. Select the AI Fragment and use Search Archive<> (FE_ALT1<>) to translate information about Interceptor's crash site to your starship's navigation systems.

DRONE_SALVAGE.Name: UI_DRONE_SALVAGE_NAME
DRONE_SALVAGE.Subtitle: UI_DRONE_SALVAGE_SUB
DRONE_SALVAGE.Description_Text:
A pane of watchful <SPECIAL>g l a s s<>, retrieved from the smoking remains of the corrupted swarm's <TECHNOLOGY>Dissonance Resonators<>. It emits more light than it reflects, casting a faint purple hue on its surroundings.

Highly sought after for salvage operations, as it can be used to bypass the security systems of key <TECHNOLOGY>Sentinel ship technologies<>.

DRONE_SHARD.Name: UI_DRONE_SHARD_NAME
DRONE_SHARD.Subtitle: UI_DRONE_SHARD_SUB
DRONE_SHARD.Description_Text:
A fragment of glassy lifeforce, chipped from a larger formation. Dynamic intermolecular binding gives the shard a strangely flexible, sinewy quality. It writhes gently, almost as if it were seeking something...

Highly sought after for salvage operations, as it can be used to bypass the security systems of key <TECHNOLOGY>Sentinel ship technologies<>.

GEODE_LAND.Name: UI_GEODE_NAME
GEODE_LAND.Subtitle: UI_GEODE_SUB
GEODE_LAND.Description_Text: An unusually vibrant and potentially valuable lump of rock. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and crack open with FE_ALT1<>.

GEODE_CAVE.Name: UI_GEODE_NAME
GEODE_CAVE.Subtitle: UI_GEODE_SUB
GEODE_CAVE.Description_Text: An unusually vibrant and potentially valuable lump of rock. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and crack open with FE_ALT1<>.

GEODE_CRYSTAL.Name: UI_GEODE_CRYSTAL_NAME
GEODE_CRYSTAL.Subtitle: UI_GEODE_CRYSTAL_SUB
GEODE_CRYSTAL.Description_Text: A crystalline shard with an unusually dense structure. Potentially highly valuable. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and crack open with FE_ALT1<>.

GEODE_SPACE.Name: UI_GEODE_SPACE_NAME
GEODE_SPACE.Subtitle: UI_GEODE_SPACE_SUB
GEODE_SPACE.Description_Text: A shard of pure crystalised Tritium<>. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and crack open with FE_ALT1<>.

GEODE_ASTEROID.Name: UI_GEODE_ASTEROID_NAME
GEODE_ASTEROID.Subtitle: UI_GEODE_ASTEROID_SUB
GEODE_ASTEROID.Description_Text: A highly valuable ore chunk, ready to be processed into Gold<>. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and crack open with FE_ALT1<>.

GEODE_RARE.Name: UI_GEODE_RARE_NAME
GEODE_RARE.Subtitle: UI_GEODE_RARE_SUB
GEODE_RARE.Description_Text: Though its surface is dirtied and dull, polishing this rock reveals a deep inner glow, a glitter beneath a subtly iridescent surface. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and crack open with FE_ALT1<>.

SCRAP_GOODS.Name: UI_SUSPECT_GOODS_NAME
SCRAP_GOODS.Subtitle: UI_SUSPECT_GOODS_SUB
SCRAP_GOODS.Description_Text: A suspicious looking parcel, acquired via an unusual transaction. The seller indicated it contained some sort of technology. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and use FE_ALT1<> to examine the contents. No refunds.

SCRAP_TECH.Name: UI_SUSPECT_TECH_NAME
SCRAP_TECH.Subtitle: UI_SUSPECT_GOODS_SUB
SCRAP_TECH.Description_Text: A suspicious looking parcel, acquired via an unusual transaction. The seller indicated it contained some sort of high-value or interesting item. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and use FE_ALT1<> to examine the contents. No refunds.

SCRAP_WEAP.Name: UI_SUSPECT_WEAP_NAME
SCRAP_WEAP.Subtitle: UI_SUSPECT_GOODS_SUB
SCRAP_WEAP.Description_Text: A suspicious looking parcel, acquired via an unusual transaction. The seller indicated it contained some sort of weapon-based technology. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and use FE_ALT1<> to examine the contents. No refunds.

POI_LOCATOR.Name: UI_POI_LOCATOR_NAME
POI_LOCATOR.Subtitle: UI_POI_LOCATOR_SUB
POI_LOCATOR.Description_Text: A single-use<> geometric beacon that probes the surrounding area for near-space anomalies<>. Such objects are highly unpredictable. Select the Detector and use Begin Scan (FE_ALT1<>) to begin the location process.

ABAND_LOCATOR.Name: UI_ABAND_LOCATOR_NAME
ABAND_LOCATOR.Subtitle: UI_ABAND_LOCATOR_SUB
ABAND_LOCATOR.Description_Text: A single-use<> receiver that scans for distress signals on freighter frequencies<>. Derelict or abandoned freighters often contain high-value salvage<>. Select the Receiver and use Tune Signal (FE_ALT1<>) to begin the location process.

ABAND_LOCATOR_X.Name: UI_ABAND_LOCATOR_X_NAME
ABAND_LOCATOR_X.Subtitle: UI_ABAND_LOCATOR_SUB
ABAND_LOCATOR_X.Description_Text: A single-use<> receiver that scans for distress signals on freighter frequencies<>. Derelict or abandoned freighters often contain high-value salvage<>. Select the Receiver and use Tune Signal (FE_ALT1<>) to begin the location process.

STONE_EYE_PROD.Name: UI_STONE_EYE_PROD_NAME
STONE_EYE_PROD.Subtitle: UI_STONE_EYE_PROD_SUB
STONE_EYE_PROD.Description_Text:
An eye of living stone: waiting, watching. A relic left by a slumbering guardian, keeping sentry over ancient creature burial grounds.

<FUEL>Warning<>: Disturbing the eye may disturb the slumber of <SPECIAL>living stone guardians<>. Ensure re-animated guardians are defeated before storing this relic in the home.

SACVENOM.Name: NEWPROD12_NAME
SACVENOM.Subtitle: DELICACY1_SUBTITLE
SACVENOM.Description_Text:
A stabilised poison gland extracted from a terrestrial urchin. The host-urchin is actually a colony of smaller proto-creatures, a formation built on years of slow growth and cooperation.

Of use both medicinally and as a delicacy in some riskier cuisines.

Can be sold at a <TECHNOLOGY>Galactic Trade Terminal<>.

GRAVBALL.Name: NEWPROD13_NAME
GRAVBALL.Subtitle: DELICACY1_SUBTITLE
GRAVBALL.Description_Text:
A supersymmetric particle cluster created by divergent super-gravitational forces. A <STELLAR>micro-rift<> is created as they form, and extraction of the orb prompts a localised reality weakening. <FUEL>Sentinel forces<> will respond to stablise any such anomaly.

Can be sold at a <TECHNOLOGY>Galactic Trade Terminal<>.

ALBUMENPEARL.Name: NEWPROD14_NAME
ALBUMENPEARL.Subtitle: DELICACY1_SUBTITLE
ALBUMENPEARL.Description_Text:
Gemstone formed over the course of centuries within the egg of a super-incubatory species. Highly ornamental, these gems are themselves living seeds, lucent grains of potential life.

Can be sold at a <TECHNOLOGY>Galactic Trade Terminal<>.

CAVECUBE.Name: NEWPROD11_NAME
CAVECUBE.Subtitle: DELICACY1_SUBTITLE
CAVECUBE.Description_Text:
An ancient object, unearthed from the depths of a planetary cave system. Its surface is cold to the touch, and is curiously polished despite its age.

A fusion of metal and rock, these cubes have proved resistant to industrial processing. As such, they are of value only to collectors.

Can be sold at a <TECHNOLOGY>Galactic Trade Terminal<>.

FIENDCORE.Name: UI_FIENDCORE_NAME
FIENDCORE.Subtitle: UI_FIENDCORE_SUB
FIENDCORE.Description_Text: A pulsating jellied orb, this gooey sphere is warm to the touch. Its stench triggers a primal fear in mortal beings, a deep-seated gnawing that begs you to drop it and flee.

STORM_CRYSTAL.Name: UI_STORMCRYSTAL_NAME
STORM_CRYSTAL.Subtitle: UI_STORMCRYSTAL_SUB
STORM_CRYSTAL.Description_Text: A rare and highly valuable cluster of storm crystals. These crystalline structures thrive in stormy conditions, and naturally attract lightning strikes, becoming spectacularly luminescent when ionised. Exclusively found on <FUEL>extreme weather planets<>.

CLAMPEARL.Name: UI_CLAMPEARL_NAME
CLAMPEARL.Subtitle: UI_CLAMPEARL_SUB
CLAMPEARL.Description_Text:
Born in the hearts of enormous glowing molluscs found deep underwater.

Unlike most pearls, this sample is no unliving calcite. Some trace of the mother-clam's consciousness remains within the gem, giving it a lingering, haunting beauty.

VENTGEM.Name: UI_VENTGEM_NAME
VENTGEM.Subtitle: UI_VENTGEM_SUB
VENTGEM.Description_Text:
Formed in the incredible, high-pressure furnace of planetary cores, these rich mineral deposits have an almost glass-like quality.

Has a wide variety of industrial uses, taking advantage of both its mineral content and its extreme strength under pressure.

FISHCORE.Name: UI_FISHCORE_NAME
FISHCORE.Subtitle: UI_FISHCORE_SUB
FISHCORE.Description_Text:
A highly-pressurised fleshy orb.

One can feel it push back when touched, a flash of bioluminescence stirring in the inky black core of this mysterious object.

EYEBALL.Name: UI_EYEBALL_NAME
EYEBALL.Subtitle: UI_EYEBALL_SUB
EYEBALL.Description_Text:
The eye is cold, almost frozen, to the touch. Nonetheless, it is impossible to escape the feeling it is somehow still alive.

Extended exposure is not recommended. Do not stare back into the eye. Do not stare back. Do not stare back.

ALLOY1.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_1_NAME
ALLOY1.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY1.Description_Text:
A lightweight and highly malleable alloy. Crafted from <EARTH>Paraffinium<> and <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<>.

In high demand on the Galactic Trade Network due to its utility in the construction of planetside outposts and facilities.

ALLOY2.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_2_NAME
ALLOY2.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY2.Description_Text:
A popular metal alloy with a wide variety of uses. 'Dirty Bronze' has shed its scientific name in favour of the popular term for its colour.

Crafted from <EARTH>Pure Ferrite<> and <EARTH>Pyrite<>.

ALLOY3.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_3_NAME
ALLOY3.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY3.Description_Text:
Combined neutral alloy with uses that range from pharmacology all the way to heavy industry. Crafted from <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Ammonia<>.

Forms the backbone of galactic alloy trading.

ALLOY4.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_4_NAME
ALLOY4.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY4.Description_Text:
Pure Ferrite alloy. Crafted from <EARTH>Pure Ferrite<> and <EARTH>Uranium<>.

Used extensively in starship freighter construction due to its sheer strength. A hardcore material popular on the Galactic Trade Network.

ALLOY5.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_5_NAME
ALLOY5.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY5.Description_Text:
Highly prized and lustrous alloy. Popular with traders of all known primary galactic races. Crafted from <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Phosphorus<>.

Easily recognisable by its bright red glow and strong magnetic field.

ALLOY6.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_6_NAME
ALLOY6.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY6.Description_Text:
Soft workable alloy favoured by artisans throughout the known galaxy. Crafted from <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Dioxite<>.

A popular trading good, with many galactic shipping paths devoted to its sale and transport.

ALLOY7.Name: UI_ALLOY_COMPLEX_1_NAME
ALLOY7.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_COMPLEX_SUBTITLE
ALLOY7.Description_Text:
Advanced and durable alloy primarily used in starship hull construction and deep-space exploration drone technology.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Herox<>, <SPECIAL>Dirty Bronze<> and <SPECIAL>Lemmium<>.

ALLOY8.Name: UI_ALLOY_COMPLEX_2_NAME
ALLOY8.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_COMPLEX_SUBTITLE
ALLOY8.Description_Text:
Advanced light metal alloy traded throughout the galactic Outer Edge. Often used in the interiors of trading shuttles to reduce weight as they ascend from planets with high gravitational fields.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Aronium<>, <SPECIAL>Magno-Gold<> and <SPECIAL>Grantine<>.

STARCHART_A.Name: UI_STARCHART_NAME
STARCHART_A.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_SUB_SECURE
STARCHART_A.Description_Text: A map of a nearby planet. A secure site of interest<> has been marked. Such sites often hold blueprints for new products<>. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display. New maps can be gained by exchanging Navigation Data<> with a Space Station Cartographer.

STARCHART_B.Name: UI_STARCHART_NAME
STARCHART_B.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_SUB_DISTRESS
STARCHART_B.Description_Text: A map of a nearby planet. The coordinates of a distress signal<> have been marked. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display. New maps can be gained by exchanging Navigation Data<> with a Space Station Cartographer.

STARCHART_C.Name: UI_STARCHART_NAME
STARCHART_C.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_SUB_HABITABLE
STARCHART_C.Description_Text: A map of a nearby planet. An inhabited outpost<> of some kind has been marked. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display. New maps can be gained by exchanging Navigation Data<> with a Space Station Cartographer.

STARCHART_D.Name: UI_STARCHART_NAME
STARCHART_D.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_SUB_ALIEN
STARCHART_D.Description_Text: A map of a nearby planet. A a relic of an ancient civilisation<> has been marked. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display. New maps can be gained by exchanging Navigation Data<> with a Space Station Cartographer.

CHART_EMPTY.Name: UI_STARCHART_EMPTY_NAME
CHART_EMPTY.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_SUB
CHART_EMPTY.Description_Text:
A map of a nearby planet.

The chart is barren, devoid of any lifesigns or indications of settled territory.

A1S6_STARMAP.Name: UI_STARCHART_NAME
A1S6_STARMAP.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_SUB
A1S6_STARMAP.Description_Text: A map of a nearby planet. A a relic of an ancient civilisation<> has been marked. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display. New maps can be gained by exchanging Navigation Data<> with a Space Station Cartographer.

TUT_STARMAP.Name: UI_STARCHART_NAME
TUT_STARMAP.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_SUB
TUT_STARMAP.Description_Text: A map of a nearby planet. The coordinates of a distress signal<> have been marked. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display. New maps can be gained by exchanging Navigation Data<> with a Space Station Cartographer.

CHART_TREASURE.Name: UI_STARCHART_TREASURE_NAME
CHART_TREASURE.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_TREASURE_SUB
CHART_TREASURE.Description_Text: A map of a nearby planet. An ancient ruined site has been marked. Excavating this site is likely to yield valuable treasures<>. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display. New maps can be gained by exchanging Navigation Data<> with a Space Station Cartographer.

CHART_HIVE.Name: UI_STARCHART_HIVE_NAME
CHART_HIVE.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_HIVE_SUB
CHART_HIVE.Description_Text: A strange, shifting map. Though hard to focus upon, this chart appears to show the location of a nearby Sentinel Pillar<>. Such Sentinel strongholds house many secrets... Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display.

CHART_ROBOT.Name: UI_STARCHART_ROBOT_NAME
CHART_ROBOT.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_ROBOT_SUB
CHART_ROBOT.Description_Text: A curious mesh of old and new technology, a hybrid between two entirely separate methods of creation. Nonetheless, this location tracing device<> appears fully functional. Select this device and use Resonate (FE_ALT1<>)<> to trace its harmonic origin.

CHART_SETTLE.Name: UI_STARCHART_SETTLE_NAME
CHART_SETTLE.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_SETTLE_SUB
CHART_SETTLE.Description_Text: A map showing the location of a nearby planetary settlement, acquired from the Space Station Cartographer<>. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display.

CHART_BUI_SETTL.Name: UI_STARCHART_BUI_SETTLE_NAME
CHART_BUI_SETTL.Subtitle: UI_STARCHART_BUI_SETTLE_SUB
CHART_BUI_SETTL.Description_Text: A map showing the location of a nearby Autophage planetary settlement, acquired from an Autophage Synthesis Terminal<>. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>)<> to pin the location in your Exosuit display.

ARTIFACT_KEY.Name: UI_ARTIFACT_KEY_NAME
ARTIFACT_KEY.Subtitle: UI_ARTIFACT_KEY_SUB
ARTIFACT_KEY.Description_Text: A key of some weight, this aged piece of wrought iron must belong in a nearby lock...

TRIDENT_KEY.Name: UI_WATERKEY_NAME
TRIDENT_KEY.Subtitle: UI_WATERKEY_SUB
TRIDENT_KEY.Description_Text:
A strange forked key, glowing with an ultraviolet light.

Despite its primitive appearance, Exosuit scanning systems reveal traces of nanite foam upon its teeth.

WAR_CURIO3.Name: UI_WAR_TABLET_NAME
WAR_CURIO3.Subtitle: UI_WAR_TABLET_SUB
WAR_CURIO3.Description_Text:
A stone tablet bearing line after line of intricate runes. The words are unintelligible, an ancient dialect forgotten by all but the oldest of the Vy'keen elders.

The hand that carved this stone must have been extraordinary. The stonework is precise, delicate - and yet perfectly conveys the unyielding aggression its writer clearly possessed.

EXP_CURIO3.Name: UI_EXP_TABLET_NAME
EXP_CURIO3.Subtitle: UI_EXP_TABLET_SUB
EXP_CURIO3.Description_Text:
A glitching, pulsing data unit. It does not seem to belong in this reality.

The cube gives the impression of a silent scream, the frozen cries of hundreds of lost minds trapped within.

STATION_KEY.Name: UI_STATION_KEY_NAME
STATION_KEY.Subtitle: UI_STATION_KEY_SUB
STATION_KEY.Description_Text:
A portable data drive containing the <STELLAR>AI override codes<> for a Space Station Core.

The importance of the station AI core ensures that such keys are both highly regulated and extremely profitable on the black market.

REP_TOKEN.Name: UI_REP_TOKEN_NAME
REP_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_REP_TOKEN_SUB
REP_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A counterfeit <TECHNOLOGY>starship registration document<>. This digital signature is guaranteed free of previous crimes or misdemeanors.

Can be used to reset any negative <STELLAR>faction standing<> records at a <TECHNOLOGY>Space Station Core<>.

NAV_DATA.Name: UI_NAV_DATA_NAME
NAV_DATA.Subtitle: UI_NAV_DATA_SUB
NAV_DATA.Description_Text:
Encoded navigation data. This highly portable data unit contains all relevant cartographical information for a planetary region.

May be traded with a <TRADEABLE>Cartographer<> aboard a Space Station in exchange for <STELLAR>usable star charts<>.

NAV_DATA_DROP.Name: UI_NAV_DROPPOD_NAME
NAV_DATA_DROP.Subtitle: UI_NAV_DATA_SUB
NAV_DATA_DROP.Description_Text: Encoded navigation data which, when properly decrypted, will reveal the location of a Drop Pod<> containing an Exosuit Inventory Upgrade<>. Select the coordinates in the inventory and use Plot Route<> (FE_ALT1<>) to pin the location in your Exosuit display.

LOG_KEY.Name: UI_LOG_FRAG_NAME
LOG_KEY.Subtitle: UI_LOG_FRAG_SUB
LOG_KEY.Description_Text:
A fragment of the encryption override sequence for a <TECHNOLOGY>freighter's emergency log<>.

Several parts of the sequence may be required to gain full access to recorded data.

ACCESS1.Name: ACCESS1_NAME
ACCESS1.Subtitle: ACCESS1_SUBTITLE
ACCESS1.Description_Text:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.

Provides access to low level restricted areas and outpost systems.

ACCESS2.Name: ACCESS2_NAME
ACCESS2.Subtitle: ACCESS2_SUBTITLE
ACCESS2.Description_Text:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.
 
Provides access to mid-tier restricted areas and outpost systems.

ACCESS3.Name: ACCESS3_NAME
ACCESS3.Subtitle: ACCESS3_SUBTITLE
ACCESS3.Description_Text:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.
 
Provides access to high level restricted areas and outpost systems.

POLICE_TOKEN.Name: POLICE_TOKEN_NAME
POLICE_TOKEN.Subtitle: POLICE_TOKEN_SUB
POLICE_TOKEN.Description_Text: A token, entitling the bearer to support from the system authorities in dealing with pirate attacks.

MIND_ARC.Name: UI_MINDARC_NAME
MIND_ARC.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
MIND_ARC.Description_Text: A strange piece of technology, a gift from beyond the stars. It shimmers in a way that suggests it is not fully in this world.

SOUL_ENGINE.Name: UI_SOULENGINE_NAME
SOUL_ENGINE.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
SOUL_ENGINE.Description_Text:
A powerful organic computing unit.

A glitching beat drives this miracle circuit, performing cycle after cycle in an endless, furious loop of calculation.

BP_SALVAGE.Name: BP_SALVAGE_NAME
BP_SALVAGE.Subtitle: BP_SALVAGE_SUB
BP_SALVAGE.Description_Text:
The salvageable heart of some ancient technology. Unreadable in its current form.

These databanks can be spent at a <TECHNOLOGY>Construction Research Unit<> and used to research new <STELLAR>Construction Blueprints<>.

FACT_TOKEN.Name: UI_FACT_TOKEN_NAME
FACT_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_FACT_TOKEN_SUB
FACT_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A portable data unit, compatible with most <STELLAR>planetary fabricator facilities<>.

Once access has been gained to a central control terminal, the Override Unit can divert the facilities resources towards researching new product recipes.

FRIG_TOKEN.Name: UI_FRIG_TOKEN_NAME
FRIG_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_FRIG_TOKEN_SUB
FRIG_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A technology module harvested from the remains of a large interstellar starship. May be collected from <STELLAR>freighter crashsites<> or salvaged during <STELLAR>frigate expeditions<>.

Useless in its current form, a <TECHNOLOGY>Research Station<> aboard your freighter may be able to convert it into useable technology.

SHIP_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_SHIP_INV_TOKEN_NAME
SHIP_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_SHIP_INV_TOKEN_SUB
SHIP_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A technology module harvested from the remains of a <STELLAR>salvaged starship<>. May also be collected from <STELLAR>freighter crash sites<> or salvaged during <STELLAR>frigate expeditions<>.

Can be used to expand starship storage capacity at the Space Station's <TECHNOLOGY>Starship Outfitter<>.

FREI_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_FREIGHT_INV_TOKEN_NAME
FREI_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_FREIGHT_INV_TOKEN_SUB
FREI_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A technology module harvested from the remains of an <STELLAR>abandoned freighter<> found floating in space. May also be salvaged during <STELLAR>frigate expeditions<>.

Pre-packed nano-expanders fill out this portable unit and graft it to an existing freighter, increasing its <STELLAR>inventory capacity<>. Apply at your freighter's <TECHNOLOGY>Upgrade Terminal<>.

WEAP_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_WEAPON_INV_TOKEN_NAME
WEAP_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_WEAPON_INV_TOKEN_SUB
WEAP_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A flexible upgrade circuit, compatible with all <STELLAR>person Multi-Tools<>.

This module can be wired into a Multi-Tool at a Space Station <STELLAR>Multi-Tool Upgrade Rack<>, granting the user more space in the Multi-Tool's internal layout to add further upgrades or technology specialisations.

SUIT_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_SUIT_INV_TOKEN_NAME
SUIT_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_SUIT_INV_TOKEN_SUB
SUIT_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text:
An advanced survival technology module that allows expansion of a user's <STELLAR>Exosuit Storage<>.

Pre-packed nano-expanders create stablised sub-warp voids within the Exosuit, increasing its <STELLAR>inventory capacity<>. Apply this augmentation at the Exosuit upgrade terminal on board a <STELLAR>Space Station<>.

ALIEN_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_ALIEN_INV_TOKEN_NAME
ALIEN_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_ALIEN_INV_TOKEN_SUB
ALIEN_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text: An additional storage nodule<> for Sentient<> starships. Upon hatching, the parasite inside this sac is grafted upon the vessel, exchanging the use of its cavernous innards for vital nutrients from the host. Use FE_ALT1<><> to trigger growth and begin the hatching process<>.

ALIEN_TECHBOX.Name: UI_ALIEN_ALLTECHBOX_NAME
ALIEN_TECHBOX.Subtitle: UI_ALIEN_ALLTECHBOX_SUB
ALIEN_TECHBOX.Description_Text: A writhing sac of genetic fluid, designed to foster the creation of new bio-infused technology<> for a sentient starship<>. The embryo will grow into bio-technology upgrade<>. Begin biogenesis<> with FE_ALT1<><>.

TECHBOX.Name: UI_TECHBOX_NAME
TECHBOX.Subtitle: UI_TECHBOX_SUB
TECHBOX.Description_Text: The shattered remnants of an expired traveller<>. It whispers, an unknowable name deep within its fibres. The memory will manifest as an important technology upgrade<> to aid you on your travels. Absorb<> this memory with FE_ALT1<><>.

INVBOX.Name: UI_INVBOX_NAME
INVBOX.Subtitle: UI_ROGUE_BOX_SUB
INVBOX.Description_Text: The shattered remnants of an expired traveller<>. It whispers, an unknowable name deep within its fibres. The memory will manifest as an inventory expansion<> to aid you on your travels. Absorb<> this memory with FE_ALT1<><>.

FRIGATE_FUEL_1.Name: UI_FREIGHTER_FUEL_1_NAME
FRIGATE_FUEL_1.Subtitle: LAUNCHFUEL_SUB
FRIGATE_FUEL_1.Description_Text:
A small barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

FRIGATE_FUEL_2.Name: UI_FREIGHTER_FUEL_2_NAME
FRIGATE_FUEL_2.Subtitle: LAUNCHFUEL_SUB
FRIGATE_FUEL_2.Description_Text:
A large barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

FRIGATE_FUEL_3.Name: UI_FREIGHTER_FUEL_3_NAME
FRIGATE_FUEL_3.Subtitle: LAUNCHFUEL_SUB
FRIGATE_FUEL_3.Description_Text:
A huge barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

FRIG_BOOST_TRA.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_TRA_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_TRA.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_TRA.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

The mind control device plugs into the ship's trading and communications systems, allowing the Fleet Commander to gain the upper hand in any negotiation.

FRIG_BOOST_EXP.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_EXP_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_EXP.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_EXP.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This powerful analytic computer overclocks the existing fleet systems, allowing for faster-than-light calculations. Heat is a problem, and the chips do not last long.

FRIG_BOOST_MIN.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_MIN_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_MIN.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_MIN.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

The mineral compressor allows fleet mining crews to liquidise the substances they extract, for both faster processing and easier transportation.

FRIG_BOOST_COM.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_COM_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_COM.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_COM.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This pack of autonomous explosives have been programmed to launch from the fleet and pilot themselves directly towards hostile vessels. Extremely dangerous.

FRIG_BOOST_SPD.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_SPD_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_SPD.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_SPD.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This powerful fuel upgrade overloads frigate engines, allowing for faster-than-usual travel.

TRA_CURIO1.Name: CURIO1_NAME
TRA_CURIO1.Subtitle: CURIO1_SUBTITLE
TRA_CURIO1.Description_Text:
A metal statuette of a creature with a coin placed in its beak.
 
Popular with many traders who see it as an emblem of fair commerce and peace.

TRA_CURIO2.Name: DELICACY1_NAME
TRA_CURIO2.Subtitle: DELICACY1_SUBTITLE
TRA_CURIO2.Description_Text:
Edible product much beloved by the Gek.
 
Allows beaked traders to release delightfully scented packets of gas for a prolonged period of time.
 
GekNip gas packets are considered an art form, and the truest representation of the Gek soul.

NIPNIPBUDS.Name: PROD_NIP_NAME
NIPNIPBUDS.Subtitle: PROD_NIP_SUBTITLE
NIPNIPBUDS.Description_Text: A pungent bud harvested from the NipNip plant, often used to produce Gek Nip.

WAR_CURIO1.Name: CURIO2_NAME
WAR_CURIO1.Subtitle: CURIO2_SUBTITLE
WAR_CURIO1.Description_Text:
A small wooden icon carved into the shape of a Sentinel drone.
 
Used by warriors to enter a temporary trance-like state that eliminates their kind's need for sleep.

WAR_CURIO2.Name: NEWPROD2_NAME
WAR_CURIO2.Subtitle: DELICACY1_SUBTITLE
WAR_CURIO2.Description_Text: Largely ceremonial weapon. A vital part of Vy'keen tradition and culture.

EXP_CURIO1.Name: CURIO3_NAME
EXP_CURIO1.Subtitle: CURIO3_SUBTITLE
EXP_CURIO1.Description_Text:
The metallic shell of a disconnected electronic lifeform that was too distant from its kind to be refreshed with a new entity.
 
Highly prized by all species, not least its own.

EXP_CURIO2.Name: NEWPROD3_NAME
EXP_CURIO2.Subtitle: DELICACY1_SUBTITLE
EXP_CURIO2.Description_Text: Device used by the Korvax for the storage of historical and cultural information.

FARMPROD1.Name: UI_FARMPROD_1_NAME
FARMPROD1.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD1.Description_Text:
Dilute acid for high current generation in diverse power cells.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Mordite<> and <TRADEABLE>Fungal Mould<>.

FARMPROD2.Name: UI_FARMPROD_2_NAME
FARMPROD2.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD2.Description_Text:
A synthetic lubricant that reduces wear and prolongs the lifespan of technologies with moving parts.

Crafted from <FUEL>Faecium<> and <TRADEABLE>Gamma Root<>.

FARMPROD3.Name: UI_FARMPROD_3_NAME
FARMPROD3.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD3.Description_Text:
Shatter-proof, scratch-resistant glass with a self-cleaning, UV-cured coating, for general construction use.

Refined from <STELLAR>Silicate<> powder. Extract silicate from the earth with a <TECHNOLOGY>Terrain Manipulator<>.

Can be crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Frost Crystals<> extracted from plants on <TECHNOLOGY>frozen<> worlds.

FARMPROD4.Name: UI_FARMPROD_4_NAME
FARMPROD4.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD4.Description_Text:
A thermal regulator produced from refined organic material. It is unique in its ability to produce, dissipate and distribute heat as required.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Solanium<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Frost Crystals<>.

FARMPROD5.Name: UI_FARMPROD_5_NAME
FARMPROD5.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD5.Description_Text:
A connective fibre for electronics, made from an advanced synthetic polymer and capable of serving as a conduit for power and data.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Cactus Flesh<> and <TRADEABLE>Star Bulbs<>.

FARMPROD6.Name: UI_FARMPROD_6_NAME
FARMPROD6.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD6.Description_Text:
A highly reactive gel, this substance is both energy-rich and dangerous to touch.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Cactus Flesh<>.

FARMPROD7.Name: UI_FARMPROD_7_NAME
FARMPROD7.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD7.Description_Text:
A general purpose high explosive, offered in liquid form for convenience of transport and deployment. Do not drink.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Acid<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Unstable Gel<>.

FARMPROD8.Name: UI_FARMPROD_8_NAME
FARMPROD8.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD8.Description_Text:
An advanced building material, this glass has been imbued with organic compounds that allow it to react to the environment. Microbes within the glass filter harmful light of all wavelengths and balance the atmosphere as required.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Lubricant<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Glass<>.

FARMPROD9.Name: UI_FARMPROD_9_NAME
FARMPROD9.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD9.Description_Text:
Stackable, semi-flexible circuit board made from a highly durable synthetic polymer.

Crafted from <COMMODITY>Heat Capacitors<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Poly Fibre<>.

REACTION1.Name: UI_REACTION_1_NAME
REACTION1.Subtitle: UI_REACTION_SUBTITLE
REACTION1.Description_Text:
A refined product, holding the energy potential of heated atmospheric gas in a stable state until required.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Sulphurine<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

REACTION2.Name: UI_REACTION_2_NAME
REACTION2.Subtitle: UI_REACTION_SUBTITLE
REACTION2.Description_Text:
A refined product, taking ordinary carbon and boosting it with radioactive energy.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Radon<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

REACTION3.Name: UI_REACTION_3_NAME
REACTION3.Subtitle: UI_REACTION_SUBTITLE
REACTION3.Description_Text:
A refined product, this is a powerful organic fertiliser in an easily distributed form.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Nitrogen<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

COMPOUND1.Name: UI_COMPOUND_1_NAME
COMPOUND1.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND1.Description_Text:
A catalytic material used in the creation of many organic fertilisers.

Crafted from <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<> and <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<>.

COMPOUND2.Name: UI_COMPOUND_2_NAME
COMPOUND2.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND2.Description_Text:
An advanced material useful in many electronic devices, with its own in-built temperature regulator.

Crafted from <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

COMPOUND3.Name: UI_COMPOUND_3_NAME
COMPOUND3.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND3.Description_Text:
A paradoxical material, made less mysterious by its relative ease of manufacture.

Crafted from <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

COMPOUND4.Name: UI_COMPOUND_4_NAME
COMPOUND4.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND4.Description_Text:
An advanced fuel source, made from a perfect blend of high potential energy organic materials.

Crafted from <FUEL>Organic Catalyst<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

COMPOUND5.Name: UI_COMPOUND_5_NAME
COMPOUND5.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND5.Description_Text:
An advanced conductive material, the superconductor further enriches the field-warping power of the Semiconductor.

Crafted from <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Semiconductors<>.

COMPOUND6.Name: UI_COMPOUND_6_NAME
COMPOUND6.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND6.Description_Text:
An advanced, self-regulating hybrid material, the Cryo-Pump distributes heat across itself with near perfect efficiency, making it vital in the creation of thermal regulators.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Hot Ice<> and <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<>

MEGAPROD1.Name: UI_MEGAPROD_1_NAME
MEGAPROD1.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
MEGAPROD1.Description_Text:
A miniature self-controlled nuclear reactor. Generates sub-stellar levels of energy in a hassle-free, widely compatible fuel module.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Liquid Explosives<> and <FUEL>Fusion Accelerant<>.

MEGAPROD2.Name: UI_MEGAPROD_2_NAME
MEGAPROD2.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
MEGAPROD2.Description_Text:
A highly advanced computational device, essential for the complex calculations involved in warp travel.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Circuit Boards<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Superconductors<>.

MEGAPROD3.Name: UI_MEGAPROD_3_NAME
MEGAPROD3.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
MEGAPROD3.Description_Text:
A low temperature chamber, designed to prevent the natural decay of organic matter.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Living Glass<> and a <TECHNOLOGY>Cryo-Pump<>.

ULTRAPROD1.Name: UI_ULTRAPROD_1_NAME
ULTRAPROD1.Subtitle: UI_ULTRAPROD_SUBTITLE
ULTRAPROD1.Description_Text:
A highly advanced piece of technology for use in the next generation of power plants. Producing a fusion core requires both intricate scientific skills and complex industrial processes.

Crafted from <FUEL>Portable Reactor<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Quantum Processors<> and <SPECIAL>Geodesite<>.

ULTRAPROD2.Name: UI_ULTRAPROD_2_NAME
ULTRAPROD2.Subtitle: UI_ULTRAPROD_SUBTITLE
ULTRAPROD2.Description_Text:
A device specifically crafted to keep lifeforms alive for thousands of years longer than their natural lifespan. Such a device requires great skill to manufacture, as not only is it technically complex, but the consequences for a user in the event of malfunction would be disastrous.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Quantum Processors<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Cryogenic Chambers<>, and <SPECIAL>Iridesite<>.

TRA_ALLOY1.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_1_NAME
TRA_ALLOY1.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_SUB
TRA_ALLOY1.Description_Text:
A packed crate of carbon nanotubes.

These tiny but incredibly strong tubes are required in the construction of tiny but incredibly strong <SPECIAL>scientific components<>.

TRA_ALLOY2.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_2_NAME
TRA_ALLOY2.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_SUB
TRA_ALLOY2.Description_Text:
A hopper of self-repairing Heridium. It looks fresh.

Used in the creation of <SPECIAL>scientific components<>. Self-repairing heridium is particularly useful for deployment in remote facilities, where maintenance opportunities may be limited or deadly.

TRA_ALLOY3.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_3_NAME
TRA_ALLOY3.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_SUB
TRA_ALLOY3.Description_Text:
Several bottles of optical solvent.

The liquid in these bottles is used to wash away surplus light that may otherwise cause decay in <SPECIAL>scientific components<>.

TRA_ALLOY4.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_4_NAME
TRA_ALLOY4.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_SUB
TRA_ALLOY4.Description_Text:
A specially manufactured container of five-dimensional tori.

Highly specific materials are required to construct shapes in extra dimensions. These tori are used to contain the strong fields generated in the manufacture of <SPECIAL>scientific components<>.

TRA_ALLOY5.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_5_NAME
TRA_ALLOY5.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ALLOY_SUB
TRA_ALLOY5.Description_Text:
A densely layered package of superconducting fibres.

Powerful, flexible, and water-resistant; the controlled magnetic weave of these fibres is vital in the creation of many <SPECIAL>scientific components<>.

TRA_COMMODITY1.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMOD_1_NAME
TRA_COMMODITY1.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMODITY_SUB
TRA_COMMODITY1.Description_Text:
A crate packed with hard drives, each of which contain vast amounts of decrypted user data.

Individually of low value, taken together these repositories can be processed and scanned for valuable data. This processing occurs in systems with <SPECIAL>advanced material<> economies.

TRA_COMMODITY2.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMOD_2_NAME
TRA_COMMODITY2.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMODITY_SUB
TRA_COMMODITY2.Description_Text:
Several spools of star silk.

Star silk is woven on enormous solar looms in orbit around trading planets. Cosmic ray impact triggers the pattern of the weave, which can then be used in <SPECIAL>advanced material<> processing.

TRA_COMMODITY3.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMOD_3_NAME
TRA_COMMODITY3.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMODITY_SUB
TRA_COMMODITY3.Description_Text:
Several canisters of comet droplets.

An elaborate trading name for chunks of meteorite, these rocks are nonetheless extremely valuable to the <SPECIAL>advanced material<> economies that can process them.

TRA_COMMODITY4.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMOD_4_NAME
TRA_COMMODITY4.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMODITY_SUB
TRA_COMMODITY4.Description_Text:
A packed crate of ion spheres.

These delicate glass spheres house a small-scale replica of the upper atmosphere. Sparkly and hypnotic to look at, these baubles are also of importance in the manufacture of <SPECIAL>advanced material<> alloys.

TRA_COMMODITY5.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMOD_5_NAME
TRA_COMMODITY5.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMMODITY_SUB
TRA_COMMODITY5.Description_Text:
A bundle of precisely calibrated teleport coordinators.

These pin-prick sized circuits are vital to the delicate process of inserting reinforcing material into <SPECIAL>advanced alloys<>. They can also aid long-distance sales efforts.

TRA_COMPONENT1.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMP_1_NAME
TRA_COMPONENT1.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMPONENT_SUB
TRA_COMPONENT1.Description_Text:
Several huge cogs.

Sturdy, well-made metal gears. While not advanced technology themselves, they're a vital component in countless pieces of <SPECIAL>high-tech<> machinery all over the galaxy.

TRA_COMPONENT2.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMP_2_NAME
TRA_COMPONENT2.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMPONENT_SUB
TRA_COMPONENT2.Description_Text:
Wrapped and greased pistons, ready for shipping.

<SPECIAL>High-tech<> components frequently require rapidly moving parts, or high-endurance motors. Without specially coated pistons, the failure rate of such parts would be significantly higher.

TRA_COMPONENT3.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMP_3_NAME
TRA_COMPONENT3.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMPONENT_SUB
TRA_COMPONENT3.Description_Text:
A crate of mesh decouplers.

The creation of <SPECIAL>high-tech<> components often involves accidental mesh-coupling. These decouplers are particularly powerful, being able to deploy six prongs simultaneously.

TRA_COMPONENT4.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMP_4_NAME
TRA_COMPONENT4.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMPONENT_SUB
TRA_COMPONENT4.Description_Text:
Packed and separated data containers for holographic crankshafts.

Real crankshafts are frequently too large, noisy or hard-to-maintain for use in delicate machines. When faced with such a situation, <SPECIAL>high-tech<> manufacturers turn to these holographic substitutes.

TRA_COMPONENT5.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMP_5_NAME
TRA_COMPONENT5.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_COMPONENT_SUB
TRA_COMPONENT5.Description_Text:
A large crate of high-capacity vector compressors.

The creation of interstellar drives often requires dimensions to be condensed and then re-rendered. Such <SPECIAL>high-tech<> component manufacture would not be possible without industrial-grade compressors such as these.

TRA_ENERGY1.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_1_NAME
TRA_ENERGY1.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_SUB
TRA_ENERGY1.Description_Text:
A crate packed with spark canisters.

Many industrial and <SPECIAL>mining<> processes have considerable power demands. A counterpart to the slow release of a battery, spark canisters are able to meet these demands instantaneously.

TRA_ENERGY2.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_2_NAME
TRA_ENERGY2.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_SUB
TRA_ENERGY2.Description_Text:
A packet of well-isolated industrial batteries.

Heavy-duty batteries are required to power deep level <SPECIAL>mining<>operations. These highly durable sources can last for weeks, even in the extremes of heat and pressure found kilometres underground.

TRA_ENERGY3.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_3_NAME
TRA_ENERGY3.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_SUB
TRA_ENERGY3.Description_Text:
Several packets of ohmic gel.

Power-hungry <SPECIAL>mining<> operations are fraught with danger. Ohmic gel helps keep rapidly moving parts both insulated and lubricated.

TRA_ENERGY4.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_4_NAME
TRA_ENERGY4.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_SUB
TRA_ENERGY4.Description_Text:
Corrosion-resistant barrels of an experimental power fluid.

One barrel of this highly volatile concoction is enough to power a space station for weeks on end. Particularly valued by <SPECIAL>mining<> economies.

TRA_ENERGY5.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_5_NAME
TRA_ENERGY5.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_ENERGY_SUB
TRA_ENERGY5.Description_Text:
A slightly glowing bundle of fusion cores.

Power source, engine, high-capacity heater. A fusion core is the ultimate in deep-space power generation. Highly valued by <SPECIAL>mining<> economies looking to make their asteroid colonies more self-sufficient.

TRA_EXOTICS1.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_1_NAME
TRA_EXOTICS1.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_SUB
TRA_EXOTICS1.Description_Text:
A loose collection of recycled pheromone bottles.

Vast quantities of pheromones are produced and distributed every day. This has spawned a lucrative <SPECIAL>trading<> opportunity for those willing to deal with the waste products. These glass jars have been thoroughly scrubbed and should pose no threat to the carrier.

TRA_EXOTICS2.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_2_NAME
TRA_EXOTICS2.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_SUB
TRA_EXOTICS2.Description_Text:
A parcel of neutron microscopes.

Scientific economies produce and consume large numbers of microscopes. However, some have slight defects that render them unsuitable for precision work. These are still a <SPECIAL>trading<> opportunity, in that they can be sold to those unable to tell the difference.

TRA_EXOTICS3.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_3_NAME
TRA_EXOTICS3.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_SUB
TRA_EXOTICS3.Description_Text:
A jumbled box of instability injectors.

Grand experiments often require a large number of variables to be changed in a very short period of time. An instability injector provides such a service. They can also be used to create chaos in market systems; such unethical behaviour represents an excellent <SPECIAL>trading<> opportunity.

TRA_EXOTICS4.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_4_NAME
TRA_EXOTICS4.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_SUB
TRA_EXOTICS4.Description_Text:
A vat of preserved organic piping. Still warm.

To avoid difficult ethical problems, many labs grow their test subjects on a component level. The leftovers can be profitable in <SPECIAL>trading<> economies with relaxed medical regulations.

TRA_EXOTICS5.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_5_NAME
TRA_EXOTICS5.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_EXOTICS_SUB
TRA_EXOTICS5.Description_Text:
A box of fresh neural ducts.

Neural ducts are temporary inserts designed for a brief boost of concentration and productivity. Useful everywhere, these are highly valued in <SPECIAL>trading<> economies where competition between workers is fierce.

TRA_MINERALS1.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_1_NAME
TRA_MINERALS1.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_SUB
TRA_MINERALS1.Description_Text:
Several tonnes of dirt.

Leftover dirt from mining operations. Residual metals can be extracted by specialists in <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> economies with the time and equipment to sift through it.

TRA_MINERALS2.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_2_NAME
TRA_MINERALS2.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_SUB
TRA_MINERALS2.Description_Text:
Large jars full of pyrite grease.

A fat solution with a high mineral content. This grease is highly valued by <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> economies, where it's used to keep large machinery oiled and glistening.

TRA_MINERALS3.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_3_NAME
TRA_MINERALS3.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_SUB
TRA_MINERALS3.Description_Text:
A crate of bromide salt.

The result of an extensive distillation and evaporation process, the bromide salt vats feed hungry factories in <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> systems.

TRA_MINERALS4.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_4_NAME
TRA_MINERALS4.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_SUB
TRA_MINERALS4.Description_Text:
A sack full of polychromatic zirconium crystals.

These crystals produce lenses of dazzling colour and near-indestructible hardness. Highly valuable in <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> economies.

TRA_MINERALS5.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_5_NAME
TRA_MINERALS5.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_MINERALS_SUB
TRA_MINERALS5.Description_Text:
A neatly wrapped parcel of re-latticed arc crystals.

Extremely rare mineral formations, arc crystals are in high demand in <SPECIAL>manufacturing<> economies, where their hardness and conductivity is vital to several industrial processes. They also make alluring (if dangerous) jewellery.

TRA_TECH1.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_1_NAME
TRA_TECH1.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_SUB
TRA_TECH1.Description_Text:
A collection of salvaged circuitry.

<SPECIAL>Power generation<> economies go through vast numbers of high-tech components. As such, the demand is present even for highly damaged circuits, to be scavenged for parts or just plugged wholesale into low-quality power cores.

TRA_TECH2.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_2_NAME
TRA_TECH2.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_SUB
TRA_TECH2.Description_Text:
Several large bars of welding soap.

Used in <SPECIAL>power generation<> systems to heat-clean metal diodes before they're fused into batteries.

TRA_TECH3.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_3_NAME
TRA_TECH3.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_SUB
TRA_TECH3.Description_Text:
A reinforced crate of ion capacitors.

These supercapacitors have an incredibly high energy density. In great demand in <SPECIAL>power generation<> economies.

TRA_TECH4.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_4_NAME
TRA_TECH4.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_SUB
TRA_TECH4.Description_Text:
A container of positioning units and associated wiring.

These APS units can be used to turn virtually any technology into a self-navigating system. Highly valuable in <SPECIAL>power generation<> economies, where they're used to remove conductive organic hands from the manufacturing process.

TRA_TECH5.Name: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_5_NAME
TRA_TECH5.Subtitle: UI_TRADE_ITEM_TECH_SUB
TRA_TECH5.Description_Text:
Several large quantum accelerator units.
 
 Capable of propelling matter at unmeasurable speeds, these units are particularly important in <SPECIAL>power generation<> economies, where they're used to compress the energy stored in high-grade batteries.

ILLEGAL_PROD1.Name: UI_ILLEGAL_PROD1_NAME
ILLEGAL_PROD1.Subtitle: UI_SMUGGLING_ITEM_SUB
ILLEGAL_PROD1.Description_Text:
Jars of murky, foul-smelling crystals. Produced in viscous evaporation traps, these organic salts are used in the manufacture of illegal pheromones.

Purchase is <SPECIAL>illegal<> at nearly all galactic trade terminals. Regular supply is only available within <FUEL>outlaw systems<>.

Selling banned goods into commercially-regulated space may be <TRADEABLE>highly profitable<>.

ILLEGAL_PROD2.Name: UI_ILLEGAL_PROD2_NAME
ILLEGAL_PROD2.Subtitle: UI_SMUGGLING_ITEM_SUB
ILLEGAL_PROD2.Description_Text:
Sealed vials of unregistered DNA samples, free of the standard biosecurity mechanisms that prevent unlawful genetic tampering.

Purchase is <SPECIAL>illegal<> at nearly all galactic trade terminals. Regular supply is only available within <FUEL>outlaw systems<>.

Selling banned goods into commercially-regulated space may be <TRADEABLE>highly profitable<>.

ILLEGAL_PROD3.Name: UI_ILLEGAL_PROD3_NAME
ILLEGAL_PROD3.Subtitle: UI_SMUGGLING_ITEM_SUB
ILLEGAL_PROD3.Description_Text:
A vat of highly volatile liquid. Its fumes are extremely flammable and a function as a powerful sedative.

Purchase is <SPECIAL>illegal<> at nearly all galactic trade terminals. Regular supply is only available within <FUEL>outlaw systems<>.

Selling banned goods into commercially-regulated space may be <TRADEABLE>highly profitable<>.

ILLEGAL_PROD4.Name: UI_ILLEGAL_PROD4_NAME
ILLEGAL_PROD4.Subtitle: UI_SMUGGLING_ITEM_SUB
ILLEGAL_PROD4.Description_Text:
A vacuum-sealed bundle of dazzlingly beautiful feathers. The animal that gave its life for this impossible, kaleidoscopic, charm is long since extinct.

Purchase is <SPECIAL>illegal<> at nearly all galactic trade terminals. Regular supply is only available within <FUEL>outlaw systems<>.

Selling banned goods into commercially-regulated space may be <TRADEABLE>highly profitable<>.

ILLEGAL_PROD5.Name: UI_ILLEGAL_PROD5_NAME
ILLEGAL_PROD5.Subtitle: UI_SMUGGLING_ITEM_SUB
ILLEGAL_PROD5.Description_Text:
A canister of the now-banned Vy'keen battle gas, traditionally inhaled on the eve of battle.

Purchase is <SPECIAL>illegal<> at nearly all galactic trade terminals. Regular supply is only available within <FUEL>outlaw systems<>.

Selling banned goods into commercially-regulated space may be <TRADEABLE>highly profitable<>.

ILLEGAL_PROD6.Name: UI_ILLEGAL_PROD6_NAME
ILLEGAL_PROD6.Subtitle: UI_SMUGGLING_ITEM_SUB
ILLEGAL_PROD6.Description_Text:
Reversed-engineered from a captured space station core, these unlicensed circuits are used in a wide range of black- and grey-market technologies.

Purchase is <SPECIAL>illegal<> at nearly all galactic trade terminals. Regular supply is only available within <FUEL>outlaw systems<>.

Selling banned goods into commercially-regulated space may be <TRADEABLE>highly profitable<>.

ILLEGAL_PROD7.Name: UI_ILLEGAL_PROD7_NAME
ILLEGAL_PROD7.Subtitle: UI_SMUGGLING_ITEM_SUB
ILLEGAL_PROD7.Description_Text:
Hacked together from the salvaged remains of Sentinel forces, these potent weapons are a favourite of outlaws across the galaxy.

Purchase is <SPECIAL>illegal<> at nearly all galactic trade terminals. Regular supply is only available within <FUEL>outlaw systems<>.

Selling banned goods into commercially-regulated space may be <TRADEABLE>highly profitable<>.

ILLEGAL_PROD8.Name: UI_ILLEGAL_PROD8_NAME
ILLEGAL_PROD8.Subtitle: UI_SMUGGLING_ITEM_SUB
ILLEGAL_PROD8.Description_Text:
Relics of the fallen Gek empire, condemned and banned by all the galaxy's major civilisations.

Purchase is <SPECIAL>illegal<> at nearly all galactic trade terminals. Regular supply is only available within <FUEL>outlaw systems<>.

Selling banned goods into commercially-regulated space may be <TRADEABLE>highly profitable<>.

ATLAS_STONE.Name: CURIO4_NAME
ATLAS_STONE.Subtitle: CURIO4_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_STONE.Description_Text:
A spherical gem that seems to pulsate with red light from its centre.
 
An extremely rare item often associated with ancient monolithic sites.

ATLAS_SEED_1.Name: ATLAS_SEED_1_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_1.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_1.Description_Text: Atlas Seed containing zonally-shifted quasi-stellar substrate. Warning: do not allow matrix to commune with this dimensional space.

ATLAS_SEED_2.Name: ATLAS_SEED_2_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_2.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_2.Description_Text: This Atlas Shell holds the remains of a parasitic space-borne lifeform, most likely of extra-dimensional origins.

ATLAS_SEED_3.Name: ATLAS_SEED_3_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_3.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_3.Description_Text: An Atlas Seed capable of resonating on humanoid telepathic frequencies; may attempt to subsume any subordinate intellect in close proximity.

ATLAS_SEED_4.Name: ATLAS_SEED_4_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_4.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_4.Description_Text: An Atlas Seed shell encompassing a void element harvested from the collapse state of the last universe. Toxic if ingested.

ATLAS_SEED_5.Name: ATLAS_SEED_5_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_5.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_5.Description_Text: Sculpted tau neutrino-boson matrix fixed within an irreplaceable Atlas Seed shell. May be semi-sentient.

ATLAS_SEED_6.Name: ATLAS_SEED_6_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_6.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_6.Description_Text: This irreplaceable Atlas Seed is a form of matter-adapted photons coalesced into physical solidity by unknown means.

ATLAS_SEED_7.Name: ATLAS_SEED_7_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_7.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_7.Description_Text: For unknown reasons, this unique Atlas Seed has been phased out of alignment with this quantum reality. Contents cannot be determined.

ATLAS_SEED_8.Name: ATLAS_SEED_8_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_8.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_8.Description_Text: Atlas Seed contains neutronium elements from a catastrophic supernova event that obliterated a sentient civilization in an earlier era.

ATLAS_SEED_9.Name: ATLAS_SEED_9_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_9.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_9.Description_Text: This one-of-a-kind Atlas Seed holds an aesthetically pleasing mathematical construct salvaged from the simulation of an alternate reality.

ATLAS_SEED_10.Name: ATLAS_SEED_10_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_10.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_10.Description_Text: An Atlas Seed containing a time-locked quantum cilia suspended in a photonic shell. No others are known to exist.

HEXCORE.Name: UI_HEX_CORE_NAME
HEXCORE.Subtitle: UI_HEX_CORE_SUB
HEXCORE.Description_Text: This strange energy orb constantly vibrates, emitting a low-frequency drone. Slight variations in the pattern repeat over and over, almost as if it is attempting to relay a message.

FISHBAIT_1.Name: UI_FISH_BAIT_1_NAME
FISHBAIT_1.Subtitle: UI_FISH_BAIT_SUB
FISHBAIT_1.Description_Text: A piece of specialist bait<>, designed to improve the size and rarity of your catch. Locate your Fishing Rig<> and begin bait application with FE_ALT1<>.

FISHBAIT_2.Name: UI_FISH_BAIT_2_NAME
FISHBAIT_2.Subtitle: UI_FISH_BAIT_SUB
FISHBAIT_2.Description_Text: A piece of specialist bait<>, designed to greatly improve the size and rarity of your catch. Locate your Fishing Rig<> and begin bait application with FE_ALT1<>.

FISHBAIT_3.Name: UI_FISH_BAIT_3_NAME
FISHBAIT_3.Subtitle: UI_FISH_BAIT_SUB
FISHBAIT_3.Description_Text: A specialist lure<>, designed to vastly improve the size and rarity of your catch. Of particular interest to anglers seeking legendary fish<>. Locate your Fishing Rig<> and begin bait application with FE_ALT1<>.

FISHBAIT_DAY.Name: UI_FISH_BAIT_DAY_NAME
FISHBAIT_DAY.Subtitle: UI_FISH_BAIT_SUB
FISHBAIT_DAY.Description_Text: A specialist lure<>, designed to attract diurnal<> fish. Locate your Fishing Rig<> and begin bait application with FE_ALT1<>.

FISHBAIT_NIGHT.Name: UI_FISH_BAIT_NIGHT_NAME
FISHBAIT_NIGHT.Subtitle: UI_FISH_BAIT_SUB
FISHBAIT_NIGHT.Description_Text: A specialist lure<>, designed to attract nocturnal<> fish. Locate your Fishing Rig<> and begin bait application with FE_ALT1<>.

FISHBAIT_STORM.Name: UI_FISH_BAIT_STORM_NAME
FISHBAIT_STORM.Subtitle: UI_FISH_BAIT_SUB
FISHBAIT_STORM.Description_Text: A specialist lure<>, designed to attract fish that are only active during storms<>. Locate your Fishing Rig<> and begin bait application with FE_ALT1<>.

BONE_TEMP.Name: UI_FOS_FINISHED_NAME
BONE_TEMP.Subtitle: UI_FOS_FINISHED_SUB
BONE_TEMP.Description_Text:
%CRE_DESC%

This <STELLAR>curated fossil exhibit<> can be sold, traded, or re-deployed within any <TECHNOLOGY>habitable base<>.

WORMBOOK.Name: UI_WORMBOOK_NAME
WORMBOOK.Subtitle: UI_WORMBOOK_SUB
WORMBOOK.Description_Text:
A translucent sheet of <STELLAR>worm-vellum<>, inscribed with a fanatical text. It writhes when touched.

'The children were the first to notice.
A thump thump thump, thundering deep below the sand.
The first worm split the sky like black lightning as it leapt overhead. 
Worm by worm, they rose from the desert. Migrating.
Every storm season, we each hope to be chosen. We arrange ourselves in lines across the desert, arms lifted to the sky.
Anyone may enter the maw.
We are all equal under the great worms.'

WORMSCROLL1.Name: UI_WORMSCROLL1_NAME
WORMSCROLL1.Subtitle: UI_WORMSCROLL_SUB
WORMSCROLL1.Description_Text:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'The worm lord towers above the dusty earth; its flesh becomes the sky.
Our pathetic shells cannot follow, cannot reach its height, cannot reach its depths.
We offer ourselves to the ground.
We beg our sacrifice accepted.'

WORMSCROLL2.Name: UI_WORMSCROLL2_NAME
WORMSCROLL2.Subtitle: UI_WORMSCROLL_SUB
WORMSCROLL2.Description_Text:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'The dust was choking. 
Our eyes reddened and watered. 
But the truth was inescapable.
The veins of the Atlas had surfaced.'

WORMSCROLL3.Name: UI_WORMSCROLL3_NAME
WORMSCROLL3.Subtitle: UI_WORMSCROLL_SUB
WORMSCROLL3.Description_Text:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'Now with every storm we beg to be chosen;
Arms to the sky, faces to the dirt, calling out with all we have!
When heavy raindrops hit the earth, the veins of Atlas answer.
The rapture of our consumption is beyond words.'

WORMSCROLL4.Name: UI_WORMSCROLL4_NAME
WORMSCROLL4.Subtitle: UI_WORMSCROLL_SUB
WORMSCROLL4.Description_Text:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'We tumble as it swallows, but grip the slick walls as best we can - 
Oh! - to reach the gizzard still awake. 
Breathe it deeply! How our lungs gurgle!
The slime clogs our noses and stings our eyes, 
though in this warm darkness, we are already blind.'

WORMSCROLL5.Name: UI_WORMSCROLL5_NAME
WORMSCROLL5.Subtitle: UI_WORMSCROLL_SUB
WORMSCROLL5.Description_Text:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'Curse the agony of regurgitation, 
Curse this this feeble flesh that still confines me!
My brethren were reborn, rising from the blessed dust as fresh tendrils. 
Glistening capillaries to the great veins, slithering away into the sand.
I will be patient. Until the next storm.'

WORMCORE.Name: UI_WORMCORE_NAME
WORMCORE.Subtitle: UI_WORMCORE_SUB
WORMCORE.Description_Text:
The coiled remains of a <SPECIAL>Hungering Tendril<>'s digestive tract. Though its meaty walls still convulse, there is surely no way for a fresh tendril to regrow from these meagre scraps...

Such specialist offal is rarely traded on the Galactic Exchange and is thus <STELLAR>highly valuable<>.

WORMPROD.Name: UI_WORMPROD_NAME
WORMPROD.Subtitle: UI_WORMPROD_SUB
WORMPROD.Description_Text:
The fragile embryo of a <SPECIAL>Hungering Tendril<>, still dripping with mucal butter. It wails and recoils when touched.

May be extracted from embryotic sacs with the aid of a <TECHNOLOGY>Visceral Synthesiser<>.

PIRATE_MAPPROD0.Name: UI_PIRATE_MAP0_NAME
PIRATE_MAPPROD0.Subtitle: UI_PIRATE_MAP_PART_SUB
PIRATE_MAPPROD0.Description_Text:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a troubled <STELLAR>freighter captain<>. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"We Blight this new galaxy, as we did the last, as we will the next!"

The data is of value to pirate faction <SPECIAL>The Blight<>, who attempted to retrieve it by violent means.

PIRATE_MAPPROD1.Name: UI_PIRATE_MAP1_NAME
PIRATE_MAPPROD1.Subtitle: UI_PIRATE_MAP_PART_SUB
PIRATE_MAPPROD1.Description_Text:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a <STELLAR>freighter<> shot down by pirate faction <SPECIAL>The Blight<>. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"The galactic tunnels belong to the Blight!"

The navigational information is corrupted, but appears to be linked to the data acquired from the <STELLAR>freighter captain<>.

PIRATE_MAPPROD2.Name: UI_PIRATE_MAP2_NAME
PIRATE_MAPPROD2.Subtitle: UI_PIRATE_MAP_PART_SUB
PIRATE_MAPPROD2.Description_Text:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a <STELLAR>starship<> crashed on an ocean bed. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"Annihilate every Traveller! All galaxies will fall to Blight!"

The navigational information is unreadable in its current state, but appears to be linked to the data acquired from the <STELLAR>freighter captain<>.

PIRATE_MAPWHOLE.Name: UI_PIRATE_MAPWHOLE_NAME
PIRATE_MAPWHOLE.Subtitle: UI_PIRATE_MAP_WHOLE_SUB
PIRATE_MAPWHOLE.Description_Text: Reassembled <COMMODITY>treasure coordinate data<>, retrieved from the victims of pirate faction <SPECIAL>The Blight<>.

PIRATE_BEACON.Name: UI_PIRATE_BEACON_NAME
PIRATE_BEACON.Subtitle: UI_PIRATE_BEACON_SUB
PIRATE_BEACON.Description_Text: An unmarked navigation beacon<>, acquired from the wreck of a downed starship. Use Activate Beacon (FE_ALT1<>) to deploy the beacon and retrace the final steps of the crashed ship.

PIRATE_INVITE.Name: UI_PIRATE_INVITE_NAME
PIRATE_INVITE.Subtitle: UI_PIRATE_INVITE_SUB
PIRATE_INVITE.Description_Text: "Glorious survivor! The promised star<> will be yours!" A Secure system pass<> bearing the mark of the 'Voice of Freedom'<>. Select the pass and use Accept Invitation (FE_ALT1<>) to pin the location in your navigation systems.

WHALE_BEACON.Name: UI_WHALE_BEACON_NAME
WHALE_BEACON.Subtitle: UI_WHALE_BEACON_SUB
WHALE_BEACON.Description_Text:
A signal receiver and amplifier, tuned to the wavelength of the unconscious mind. It is every colour all at once, splitting the surrounding light into a shimmering rainbow.

<FUEL>Warning:<> Carrying this antenna into deep space may attract the attention of <SPECIAL>cosmic megafauna<>.

S8_BEACON.Name: UI_S8_FRE_BEACON_NAME
S8_BEACON.Subtitle: UI_S8_FRE_BEACON_SUB
S8_BEACON.Description_Text: A makeshift device, cobbled from salvaged electronic components kept in deep storage for many years. This jumble of wires will attempt to make contact with the last-known remnants of the freighter's homeworld. Select the device and select Broadcast (FE_ALT1<>) to begin the location process.

SALVAGE_TECHMT1.Name: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_1_NAME
SALVAGE_TECHMT1.Subtitle: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_MT_SUB
SALVAGE_TECHMT1.Description_Text:
A valuable piece of recycled Multi-Tool technology, created by a <TECHNOLOGY>Multi-Tool Decommissioning Terminal<> aboard the <SPECIAL>Space Anomaly<>.

Component is useful only as scrap to be sold at a <VAL_ON>Trade Terminal<>.

SALVAGE_TECHMT2.Name: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_2_NAME
SALVAGE_TECHMT2.Subtitle: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_MT_SUB
SALVAGE_TECHMT2.Description_Text:
A valuable piece of recycled Multi-Tool technology, created by a <TECHNOLOGY>Multi-Tool Decommissioning Terminal<> aboard the <SPECIAL>Space Anomaly<>.

Component is useful only as scrap to be sold at a <VAL_ON>Trade Terminal<>.

SALVAGE_TECHMT3.Name: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_3_NAME
SALVAGE_TECHMT3.Subtitle: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_MT_SUB
SALVAGE_TECHMT3.Description_Text:
A valuable piece of recycled Multi-Tool technology, created by a <TECHNOLOGY>Multi-Tool Decommissioning Terminal<> aboard the <SPECIAL>Space Anomaly<>.

Component is useful only as scrap to be sold at a <VAL_ON>Trade Terminal<>.

SALVAGE_TECHMT4.Name: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_4_NAME
SALVAGE_TECHMT4.Subtitle: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_MT_SUB
SALVAGE_TECHMT4.Description_Text:
A valuable piece of recycled Multi-Tool technology, created by a <TECHNOLOGY>Multi-Tool Decommissioning Terminal<> aboard the <SPECIAL>Space Anomaly<>.

Component is useful only as scrap to be sold at a <VAL_ON>Trade Terminal<>.

SALVAGE_TECHMT5.Name: UI_SALVAGE_TECH_MT_5_NAME
