BIOSHIP_STEM1.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_STEM1_NAME
BIOSHIP_STEM1.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_STEM_SUB
BIOSHIP_STEM1.Description_Text:
A delicate web of living tissue, this is the spark that will ignite a new lifeform into existence.

It requires careful attendance while it matures.

BIOSHIP_STEM2.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_STEM2_NAME
BIOSHIP_STEM2.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_STEM_SUB
BIOSHIP_STEM2.Description_Text:
Though nothing more than a cluster of cells, it is already possible to detect the soft beating of this proto-heart.

It requires careful attendance while it matures.

BIOSHIP_STEM3.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_STEM3_NAME
BIOSHIP_STEM3.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_STEM_SUB
BIOSHIP_STEM3.Description_Text:
Translucent and impossibly thin, this shell is no more than the merest breath of glass. And yet the potential is clear, a relentless multiplicative hardening adding constantly to its strength.

It requires careful attendance while it matures.

BIOSHIP_STEM4.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_STEM4_NAME
BIOSHIP_STEM4.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_STEM4_SUB
BIOSHIP_STEM4.Description_Text:
A slow knitting together of flesh, neurons and antimatter. The way this mind experiences the universe is beyond any imagining.

It requires careful attendance while it matures.

BIOSHIP_GROWTH1.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_GROWTH1_NAME
BIOSHIP_GROWTH1.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_GROWTH_SUB
BIOSHIP_GROWTH1.Description_Text:
This web of living tissue has grown its own metallic filaments, a mesh of silver and flesh. It crackles with its own electric charge, a network in need of its nodes.

It awaits its host.

BIOSHIP_GROWTH2.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_GROWTH2_NAME
BIOSHIP_GROWTH2.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_GROWTH_SUB
BIOSHIP_GROWTH2.Description_Text:
Powerful and muscular, this bionic pump sits within a network of synthetic tubes. It twitches when touched, its rhythms sensitive to the presence of other thinking entities.

It awaits its host.

BIOSHIP_GROWTH3.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_GROWTH3_NAME
BIOSHIP_GROWTH3.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_GROWTH_SUB
BIOSHIP_GROWTH3.Description_Text:
Translucent, reflective, iridescent, impossibly strong. This shell swiftly reconfigures itself upon damage, knitting itself back together stronger than ever before. The newly formed bonds create a memory in glass, reflecting back the light absorbed at the moment of damage.

It awaits its host.

BIOSHIP_GROWTH4.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_GROWTH4_NAME
BIOSHIP_GROWTH4.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_GROWTH_SUB
BIOSHIP_GROWTH4.Description_Text:
A sensitive arrangement of neurons in a stable orbit around a miniature black hole. The mind at the heart of this bionic miracle is free from the constraints of linear time, its experience an impossible web of myriad collected lifeforms.

It awaits its host.

BIOSHIP_EGG1.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG1_NAME
BIOSHIP_EGG1.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG1_SUB
BIOSHIP_EGG1.Description_Text:
An anomalous egg. Since the encounter with the bizarre deep-space 'creature', its strange music has grown more active, more agitated.

When touched, conjures a powerful vision of a world beset by <SPECIAL>powerful anomalies<> and <STELLAR>strange colours<>.

BIOSHIP_EGG2.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG2_NAME
BIOSHIP_EGG2.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG2_SUB
BIOSHIP_EGG2.Description_Text:
An anomalous egg. Since the encounter with the bizarre deep-space 'creature', its strange music has grown more active, more agitated.

When touched, conjures a powerful vision of a <STELLAR>dust-covered world<> of <FUEL>extreme storms<>.

BIOSHIP_EGG3.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG3_NAME
BIOSHIP_EGG3.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG3_SUB
BIOSHIP_EGG3.Description_Text:
An anomalous egg. Since the encounter with the bizarre deep-space 'creature', its strange music has grown more active, more agitated.

When touched, conjures a powerful vision of a <TECHNOLOGY>water world<> covered in <TRADEABLE>lush and verdant plantlife<>.

BIOSHIP_EGG4.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG4_NAME
BIOSHIP_EGG4.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG4_SUB
BIOSHIP_EGG4.Description_Text:
An anomalous egg. Since the encounter with the bizarre deep-space 'creature', its strange music has grown more active, more agitated.

When touched, conjures a powerful visions of a planet of strange anomalies, one minute a world of grass, the next a world of bizarre fungal growths...

BIOSHIP_EGG5.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG4_NAME
BIOSHIP_EGG5.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_EGG4_SUB
BIOSHIP_EGG5.Description_Text: An anomalous egg. Since the encounter with the bizarre deep-space 'creature', its strange music has grown more active, more agitated. When touched, conjures a powerful visions of pink and blue, colours seared into the mind of the holder. BIOSHIP_COMP1.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP1_NAME
BIOSHIP_COMP1.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP1_SUB
BIOSHIP_COMP1.Description_Text:
A <STELLAR>biomechanical construct<>, created to the design of an anonymous host.

This device appears to offer an interface between an individual entity and a greater shared consciousness. It appears derived from, but not attuned to, Korvax technology.

BIOSHIP_COMP2.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP2_NAME
BIOSHIP_COMP2.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP2_SUB
BIOSHIP_COMP2.Description_Text:
A <STELLAR>biomechanical construct<>, created to the design of an anonymous host.

Organic, but aglow with heat and possessing a highly-pressurised inner vessel. This 'device' is part pump, and part accelerated evolutionary chamber.

BIOSHIP_COMP3.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP3_NAME
BIOSHIP_COMP3.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP3_SUB
BIOSHIP_COMP3.Description_Text:
A <STELLAR>biomechanical construct<>, created to the design of an anonymous host.

A fine mesh of tightly woven fibre. Micro-organisms embedded within the weave allow it to regenerate endlessly, a perfect and infinite bionic skin.

BIOSHIP_COMP4.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP4_NAME
BIOSHIP_COMP4.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP4_SUB
BIOSHIP_COMP4.Description_Text:
A <STELLAR>biomechanical construct<>, created to the design of an anonymous host.

Capsules of genetic material, encased in a film of living glass. Shared memories swim in the their reflective surfaces, waiting for their chance to shape the life within.

BIOSHIP_COMP5.Name: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP5_NAME
BIOSHIP_COMP5.Subtitle: UI_BIOSHIP_COMP5_SUB
BIOSHIP_COMP5.Description_Text:
A <STELLAR>biomechanical construct<>, created to the design of an anonymous host.

A fusion of complex circuitry and the ineffable glitch of the Traveller. Such a calculus might bind realities together, or tear them into mere simulated fragments.

EXOTIC_BIOPROD.Subtitle: UI_BIO_EXOTIC_SUB_SUB
EXOTIC_BIOPROD.Description_Text:
Unusual surface interactions cause this liquid to quickly split into small, perfect, spheres. Light refracted through one such sphere splits into colours beyond description.

Of <TECHNOLOGY>unknown origin<>.

MP_REP_PART1.Name: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART1_NAME
MP_REP_PART1.Subtitle: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART_SUB
MP_REP_PART1.Description_Text:
An advanced nanocomputer, performing processing tasks related to starship navigation, flight stabilisation, and external sensors.

This part could be in working order, but will require <SPECIAL>decryption<> before it can be installed in a new ship. A paired <STELLAR>decryption terminal<> can be located via Exosuit analysis.

MP_REP_PART1B.Subtitle: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART_SUB

MP_REP_PART1C.Subtitle: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART_SUB
MP_REP_PART1C.Description_Text:
An advanced nanocomputer, performing processing tasks related to starship navigation, flight stabilisation, and external sensors.

The part appears intact, functional, and ready to be installed in a new ship.

MP_REP_PART2.Name: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART2_NAME
MP_REP_PART2.Subtitle: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART_SUB
MP_REP_PART2.Description_Text:

MP_REP_PART3.Subtitle: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART_SUB
MP_REP_PART3.Description_Text:

MP_REP_PART3B.Subtitle: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART_SUB

MP_REP_PART3C.Subtitle: UI_MP_REPAIR_PART_SUB

DRONE_BROKEN.Name: UI_DRONE_BROKEN_NAME
DRONE_BROKEN.Subtitle: UI_DRONE_BROKEN_SUB
DRONE_BROKEN.Description_Text:
The shell of a <SPECIAL>Sentinel drone<>, all that remains after its destruction in combat. While the exterior is physically intact, its internals have been severely burned.

Given the right tools and several exotic components, it may be possible to <TECHNOLOGY>repair<> it.

DRONE_PART_E2.Name: UI_DRONE_PART_E2_NAME
DRONE_PART_E2.Subtitle: UI_DRONE_PART_SUB
DRONE_PART_E2.Description_Text:
A thin, <STELLAR>shimmering thread<>, once owned by Iteration: Gemini. This impossible fibre, once a treasured keepsake, sings on the wavelength of the Space Anomaly.

A valuable and exotic component, this would be of great use to Iteration: Tethys in <TECHNOLOGY>repairing<> the shattered Drone.

DRONE_PART_E3.Name: UI_DRONE_PART_E3_NAME
DRONE_PART_E3.Subtitle: UI_DRONE_PART_SUB
DRONE_PART_E3.Description_Text:
A vial of the portal's <TECHNOLOGY>blue amber<>, given to you by Iteration: Mercury. The ether of the Atlas itself, this is primeval liquid from which it weaves the multiverse.

A valuable and exotic component, this would be of great use to Iteration: Tethys in <TECHNOLOGY>repairing<> the shattered Drone.

DRONE_PART_P.Name: UI_DRONE_PART_POLO_NAME
DRONE_PART_P.Subtitle: UI_DRONE_PART_SUB
DRONE_PART_P.Description_Text:
A handful of <SPECIAL>glassy orbs<>, once owned by Specialist Polo. Their pearlescent surface does not reflect the world around them, offering instead a mirror to different reality.

A valuable and exotic component, this would be of great use to Iteration: Tethys in <TECHNOLOGY>repairing<> the shattered Drone.

DRONE_FRIEND.Name: UI_DRONE_FRIEND_NAME
DRONE_FRIEND.Subtitle: UI_DRONE_FRIEND_SUB
DRONE_FRIEND.Description_Text: A specialist device, created by Iteration Tethys. Its primary function is to hail your reconstructed Sentinel drone<>. Select the device and use Activate Flare<> (FE_ALT1<>) to signal [The Drone<>]. While this flare is active in your Exosuit inventory<>, the drone will stay by your side while planetside.

DRONE_FRIEND_X.Name: UI_DRONE_FRIEND_X_NAME
DRONE_FRIEND_X.Subtitle: UI_DRONE_FRIEND_SUB
DRONE_FRIEND_X.Description_Text: A specialist device, created by Iteration Tethys. Its primary function is to hail your reconstructed Sentinel drone<>. Select the device and use Deactivate Broadcast (FE_ALT1<>) to stop signalling [ The Sentry ]. While this flare is active in your Exosuit inventory<>, the drone will stay by your side while planetside.

WALKER_PROD_2.Name: UI_WALKER_PROD_2_NAME
WALKER_PROD_2.Subtitle: SUB_DEADDRONE_SUBTITLE
WALKER_PROD_2.Description_Text:
Shifting nanite clusters sewn together with a <SPECIAL>pugneum filament<>, this circuit is painfully hot to the touch. A sinister purple light leaks from deep within its wiring, changing in intensity as it watches its holder.

Unlike most Walker brains, this one has survived its violent extraction and is <TECHNOLOGY>pristine<> and <TECHNOLOGY>undamaged<>. It could potentially be installed in a new vessel...

WALKER_PROD_3.Name: UI_WALKER_PROD_3_NAME
WALKER_PROD_3.Subtitle: SUB_DEADDRONE_SUBTITLE
WALKER_PROD_3.Description_Text:
Shifting nanite clusters sewn together with a <SPECIAL>pugneum filament<>, this circuit is painfully hot to the touch. The purple light that leaks from within its wiring has softened, as if it has become less hostile.

Previously embedded within a Sentinel Walker, this semi-organic computer has been altered by <STELLAR>Iteration: Tethys<>. Its new-found freedom from the Atlas has been <FUEL>noted<> by the universe.

WALKER_PROD_4.Name: UI_WALKER_PROD_4_NAME
WALKER_PROD_4.Subtitle: SUB_DEADDRONE_SUBTITLE
WALKER_PROD_4.Description_Text:
Shifting nanite clusters sewn together with a <SPECIAL>pugneum filament<>, this circuit is painfully hot to the touch. The purple light that leaks from within its wiring has softened, as if it has become less hostile.

Previously embedded within a Sentinel Walker, this semi-organic computer has been altered by both <STELLAR>Iteration: Tethys<> and a <FUEL>Messenger of the Atlas<>.

SHIPBRAIN_CLEAN.Name: UI_SHIP_BRAIN_CLEAN_NAME
SHIPBRAIN_CLEAN.Subtitle: UI_SHIP_BRAIN_CLEAN_SUB
SHIPBRAIN_CLEAN.Description_Text:
The central processing unit of a Sentinel interceptor ship. The circuitry appears stable, pulsing with a regular electrical heartbeat. It no longer reacts angrily to my presence.

Status: <TRADEABLE>DOCILE<>

Install this unit in a disabled Sentinel ship to unlock its vestigial cockpit and enable <STELLAR>manual piloting<>.

GAS_BRAIN_LOC.Name: UI_GAS_BRAIN_LOCATOR_NAME
GAS_BRAIN_LOC.Subtitle: UI_GAS_BRAIN_LOCATOR_SUB
GAS_BRAIN_LOC.Description_Text: A single-use<> device for locating a deep-space Gaseous Sentience<>. The lure generates an electromagnetic field of an intriguing nature to these highly advanced lifeforms. Select the Lure and use Generate Field (FE_ALT1<>) to begin the location process.

ROGUE_G_STONE1.Name: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_NAME1
ROGUE_G_STONE1.Subtitle: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_SUB
ROGUE_G_STONE1.Description_Text:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The leviathan was like nothing I've ever seen.
So vast as to blot out the sun.
I wanted it. I deserve to have it! It will be mine.
But it resisted, would not come quietly.
It wailed and it wailed as the infra-knife carved into its meat.
It almost took me down with it. Perhaps it has. Perhaps..."

ROGUE_G_STONE2.Name: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_NAME2
ROGUE_G_STONE2.Subtitle: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_SUB
ROGUE_G_STONE2.Description_Text:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The same nightmare chases me: a wail fills my cockpit, the dashboard controls gummed with blood.
I have given up sleep. I pulse past blurred stars.
And then there it was: majestic, drifting in the ocean of space.
Something inside me burns for it. I must have it.
Its great fin flexed toward my ship, and my hull was gone..."

ROGUE_G_STONE3.Name: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_NAME3
ROGUE_G_STONE3.Subtitle: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_SUB
ROGUE_G_STONE3.Description_Text:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"Today should have been the day. Their hour was at hand.
It must be mine. They are like nothing I've ever seen.
Everything was prepared. But it moved faster than I thought possible. As though it knew where I would fly, before I knew it myself.
A great tentacle hugged my ship, my cockpit - pressing my suit down to the bone. This suit will be my grave."

ROGUE_G_STONE4.Name: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_NAME4
ROGUE_G_STONE4.Subtitle: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_SUB
ROGUE_G_STONE4.Description_Text:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The chase is over, and I have lost.
The giants will endure, and I will end.
As I plummeted from the sky, I saw another ship falling alongside mine. Then another, and another.
I may have imagined it. The misfiring of a dying mind...
Those creatures were so beautiful. But it is all ended now.
They will haunt my thoughts no longer."

ROGUE_G_STONE5.Name: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_NAME5
ROGUE_G_STONE5.Subtitle: UI_ROGUE_GRAVE_STONE_SUB
ROGUE_G_STONE5.Description_Text:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"I came face-to-face with a creature more beautiful and bizarre than anything I have ever seen.
Despite no discernible eyes, I do not believe it is blind.
It was huge, glorious, serene. But then - with a flick of its tentacles, it was gone.
I have thought of nothing else since. I can only think of the whale. whale. whale. <SPECIAL>wail<>."

DS 2448 :: <SPECIAL>[Redacted]<>
DS 2464 :: <STELLAR>Utopia Project launched.<>
DS 2464 :: <STELLAR>Facility <><TRADEABLE>restored<><STELLAR>. Plasma deep drill rig operational. Trade routes re-opened.<>
DS 2480 :: <SPECIAL>[Redacted]<>
DS 2496 :: <STELLAR>Facility <><TRADEABLE>restored<><STELLAR>. Plasma deep drill rig operational. Trade routes re-opened.<>
DS 2512 :: <SPECIAL>[Redacted]<>

S10_ATLAS_SEED4.Name: S10_ATLAS_SEED_4_NAME
S10_ATLAS_SEED4.Subtitle: S10_ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
S10_ATLAS_SEED4.Description_Text: A seed of creation, a tiny drop of the infinity of the Atlas. Though a mere speck, this seed contains the potential for an entire universe; a boundless, glorious expansion. Use FE_ALT1<><> to resonate<> the seed, converting its waveform into the audible range.

S10_ATLAS_SEED5.Name: S10_ATLAS_SEED_5_NAME
S10_ATLAS_SEED5.Subtitle: S10_ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
S10_ATLAS_SEED5.Description_Text: A seed of creation, a perfect droplet of infinity. A gift from the Atlas, this is a tiny fragment of all the universe's dreams, will, power and life; a fragment of the Travellers; a fragment of myself. Use FE_ALT1<><> to resonate<> the seed, converting its waveform into the audible range.

S10_SOUL.Subtitle: UI_S10_SOUL_SUB

The <TECHNOLOGY>Seed<> is an echo of life, the last reverberations of a living being.

This sentience was fused with a lattice of <SPECIAL>Atlantideum<>, as though it had germinated together with the crystal.

S10_FRAGMENT.Name: S10_FRAGMENT_NAME
S10_FRAGMENT.Subtitle: S10_FRAGMENT_SUB

A shifting vortex of <SPECIAL>atlantideum<>, attuned to the growing collective will housed inside Nada's <STELLAR>Prime Terminal<>. Current sentience threshold: <STELLAR>??%<>.

The grains oscillate in a pattern, but the message is unintelligible.

S15_BOT_4.Name: UI_FISH_TRASH_BOTTLE_NAME
S15_BOT_4.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_BOT_4.Description_Text: A sealed bottle, found floating in the water. There appears to be a message from the Angler<> inside. Use FE_ALT1<><> to unseal<> the bottle and read the message within.

S15_MESSAGE0.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE0.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE0.Description_Text:
A message recovered from a bottle stowed beneath the seat of the starship. It reads:

<VAL_ON>"I finally feel like I'm getting closer. A trader on Gisto offered me solid-gold information on its location, for a price.
And so I'm selling my ship. I'll miss the <VAL_ON>Celeste<>, but I have to know if the rumours are true. I hope whoever buys you takes good care of you..."
%PARTY_1%<>

S15_MESSAGE1.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE1.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE1.Description_Text:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

<VAL_ON>"The rumours were true. It's out there, I can feel it. Not here, but somewhere. The water calls to me, I just need to follow its voice..."
%PARTY_3%<>

S15_MESSAGE2.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE2.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE2.Description_Text:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

<VAL_ON>"I saw it in my dreams last night. Scales like fire and eyes of pure starlight. It sang to me, a song of hope and longing. It wants me to find it, I know it. I must be closing in."
%PARTY_4%<>

S15_MESSAGE3.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE3.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE3.Description_Text:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

<VAL_ON>"I was right! It was here! After all these light years, all the doubts, it's finally mine. Oh, and how it shines! Like fire in the water, beautiful, impossible..."
%PARTY_5%<>

S15_MESSAGE4.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE4.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE4.Description_Text:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

<VAL_ON>"The fire has faded from my catch's scales, and my dreams have soured. I thrash through the night. My skin itches, damp and clammy. Salt seeps from my pores.
It longs to be free. I cannot keep it contained like this. It must be free.
I must be free..."<>

S15_FISH.Name: UI_S15_FISH_NAME
S15_FISH.Subtitle: UI_FISH_LEGEND_SUB
S15_FISH.Description_Text:
Fire dances across the scales of this impossible marine being. Its starlit eyes stare back at you with a meaning far deeper than any fish should know. As they stare, the world around you fades away.

The sound of water fills your ears. It wants to be free. You want to be free...

SPOOK_JUICE.Name: UI_SPOOK_JUICE_NAME
SPOOK_JUICE.Subtitle: UI_SPOOK_JUICE_SUB
SPOOK_JUICE.Description_Text: A slight membrane has begun to form over this viscous purple liquid. Beneath its glassy surface it swirls slowly, forming syrupy currents of its own accord. The elixir will maintain your local boundary integrity<> and prevent the intrusion of the horrors beyond<>. Consume the elixir with FE_ALT1<> or inject it directly into the Anomaly Suppressor<> from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

PORTAL_JUICE.Name: UI_PORTAL_JUICE_NAME
PORTAL_JUICE.Subtitle: UI_PORTAL_JUICE_SUB
PORTAL_JUICE.Description_Text: The liquid's silvered surface forms a perfect mirror, your own face reflected back as you examine it. But the more you stare, the less perfect the mirror becomes. The face in the image moves. It blinks. It - Consume the elixir with FE_ALT1<> to reveal the location of nearby portals<>.

MESSAGE_JUICE.Name: UI_MESSAGE_JUICE_NAME
MESSAGE_JUICE.Subtitle: UI_MESSAGE_JUICE_SUB
MESSAGE_JUICE.Description_Text: Thick and warm, the liquid in this jar is both deeply comforting and deeply unsettling, both familiar and repulsive at the same time. A shape forms in the surface, impossible and yet unmistakeable: PR_10<><>. Present the elixir at a portal<>, or consume it with FE_ALT1<> to commune with those beyond the boundaries of reality.

BOSS_JUICE.Name: UI_BOSS_JUICE_NAME
BOSS_JUICE.Subtitle: UI_BOSS_JUICE_SUB
BOSS_JUICE.Description_Text: The water in this vessel seems to stretch on forever, plunging down to dizzying depths, far beyond what the container could possibly hold. Consume the elixir with FE_ALT1<>. Beware what lurks in the deep water...

PURPM_PACKET.Description_Text:
The howling of an advanced intelligence banished to oblivion, a reverberation in sentience and crystal. 

Each memory in this <TECHNOLOGY>data packet<> is an entire reality in itself, bearing the fingerprint of countless lives. The <FUEL>Atlas<> will recognise this seed.

SPEC_SENTPACK.Subtitle: UI_BACKPACK2_SUB
SPEC_SENTPACK.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

A titanium flightpack, assembled from technology stolen from the Sentinel horde. Its engines are precooled with a constant flow of pugneum and nitrogen, ensuring fuel-efficient and deadly silent operation.

<FUEL>Warning<>: do not unseal pugneum containment chamber without protective gear.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

SPEC_HOOD01.Name: UI_SPEC_HOOD01_NAME
SPEC_HOOD01.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_HOOD_SUB
SPEC_HOOD01.Description_Text:
A flowing silken shroud, bestowed upon those who would sing with <SPECIAL>Voice of Freedom<>.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit with this exclusive <STELLAR>Appearance Override<> at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

TGA_SHIP01.Name: UI_SHIP_TGA_NAME
TGA_SHIP01.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_SHIP_SUB
TGA_SHIP01.Description_Text: An exclusive reforged starship<>, commemorating a time when Travellers old and new joined together to voyage across the stars. This unusual ship is optimised for effortless gliding during flight, while a localised vector field allows the craft to hover above solid planes. Claim<> this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

SWITCH_SHIP01.Name: UI_SWIT_SHIP_01_NAME
SWITCH_SHIP01.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_SHIP_SUB
SWITCH_SHIP01.Description_Text: An exclusive Starship<>. This compact fighter craft boasts superior manoeuvrability, giving it an edge in space combat. Claim<> this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

SWITCH_GUN01.Name: UI_SWIT_GUN_01_NAME
SWITCH_GUN01.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_GUN_SUB
SWITCH_GUN01.Description_Text: An exclusive Multi-Tool<>. This brightly-coloured rifle offers the user cutting-edge defensive capabilities in ground combat situations. Take<> this Multi-Tool to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current Multi-Tool. Swap between active Multi-Tools from the Utilities section of the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

EXPD_BACKPACK01.Name: UI_EXPD_BACKPACK_01_NAME
EXPD_BACKPACK01.Subtitle: UI_BACKPACK2_SUB
EXPD_BACKPACK01.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

A streamlined and lightweight backpack unit, featuring an elegant single-thruster design. This exclusive exosuit augmentation commemorates completion of the inaugural <STELLAR>Expedition<>, 'Pioneers'.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

EXPD_HELMET01.Name: UI_EXPD_HELMET_01_NAME
EXPD_HELMET01.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_HAT_SUB
EXPD_HELMET01.Description_Text:
An aggressive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>, modeled on the war helmets of the ancient Gek. This special edition is cast in a durable and precious alloy.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

EXPD_SHIP01.Name: UI_EXPD_SHIP_01_NAME
EXPD_SHIP01.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_SHIP_SUB
EXPD_SHIP01.Description_Text: An exclusive golden edition of the iconic Alpha Vector Starship<>, commemorating completion of the inaugural Expedition<>, 'Pioneers'. This highly-manoeuvrable spacecraft is constructed from a durable and precious alloy, and coated in a tough layer of fibrous insulation to endure many lifetimes' worth of rigorous space exploration. Claim<> this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

EXPD_TITLE01.Name: UI_EXPD_TITLE_01_NAME
EXPD_TITLE01.Subtitle: UI_SPEC_TITLE_SUB

Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

EXPD_SPEC02.Name: UI_EXPD_SPEC_02_NAME
EXPD_SPEC02.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_SPEC_SUB
EXPD_SPEC02.Description_Text:
The <TECHNOLOGY>SSV Normandy SR1<> is a one-of-a-kind 'deep scout' frigate. This legendary ship represents peace and cooperation between races, and commemorates completion of the 'Beachhead' <STELLAR>Expedition<>.

Recruiting this frigate will add it to your fleet. Manage your frigate fleet from a <TECHNOLOGY>Fleet Command Room<> aboard your freighter, and consult your <TECHNOLOGY>Navigator<> to deploy frigates on lucrative expeditions.

MYSTERY_TRACKER.Name: UI_MYSTERY_TRACKER_NAME
MYSTERY_TRACKER.Subtitle: UI_MYSTERY_TRACKER_SUB
MYSTERY_TRACKER.Description_Text:
Nada has detected a new pattern emerging in the stories of the <TRANS_TRA>Gek<>, <TRANS_EXP>Korvax<>, and <TRANS_WAR>Vy'keen<>.

The dosimeter measures exposure to <SPECIAL>historiographical flux<> around key artifact sites. Recordings of unusual historical shifts will enable Nada to trace the signal.

Assist Nada and Polo in their research by using this device to <STELLAR>transmit historial data<> from alien artifact sites.

A small, self-contained, perpetual motion device generates the small amount of power required to continue the projection.

BLD_FLYJAR.Subtitle: BLD_FLYJAR_SUB
BLD_FLYJAR.Description_Text:

Pre-installed bioluminescent insects provide a soft, flickering light, perfect for those seeking natural lighting for their base.

EXPD_TITLE03.Subtitle: UI_SPEC_TITLE_SUB

Specially conditioned oil is added to the jetpack's exhaust jets, creating a stream of pearlescent bubbles as it operates.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

JETS_WORM.Name: UI_WORMTRAIL_NAME
JETS_WORM.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB
JETS_WORM.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Attaches an active bio-chamber to the Jetpack's exhaust nozzles. During flight, the thrusters warm and expel the slimy juice contained within.
<STELLAR>Note<>: Contains living worms. Ejected worms may infest local ecosystems.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

EXPD_EGG_03.Name: UI_EXPD_EGG_03_NAME
EXPD_EGG_03.Subtitle: UI_EXPD_EGG_03_SUB
EXPD_EGG_03.Description_Text:
A living, fertile egg, <TRADEABLE>ready to hatch!<>

A shadow writhes beneath the egg's protective membrane.

Scans indicate the being within has the genetic potential to be <FUEL>nightmarish<> and <FUEL>soul-consuming<>.

EXPD_EGG_04.Name: UI_EXPD_EGG_04_NAME
EXPD_EGG_04.Subtitle: UI_EXPD_EGG_04_SUB
EXPD_EGG_04.Description_Text:
A living, fertile egg, <TRADEABLE>ready to hatch!<>

Curled within the shell is a hungry wormlet, its coils rippling restlessly.

Scans indicate the being within has the genetic potential to be <FUEL>cursed<> and <FUEL>insatiable<>.

BLD_SKULL.Name: BLD_WORMSKULL_NAME
BLD_SKULL.Subtitle: BLD_WORMSKULL_SUB
BLD_SKULL.Description_Text:
An exclusive buildable base ornament.

This many-toothed skull once belonged to a large legless vertebrate, cousin to the titan sandworm. The powerful jaws can exert enough force to crush a Multi-Tool, and the bones of most creatures.

EXPD_WORMHAT.Name: UI_WORMHAT_NAME
EXPD_WORMHAT.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_HAT_SUB
EXPD_WORMHAT.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Redistribute your facial organs and alarm other explorers by assuming the appearance of a sandworm cultist. This bio-silicone helmet is sealed against all known planetary hazards, but may feel slightly clammy to the wearer.

Ritualistically transform the head of your <STELLAR>Vy'keen<> appearance at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

JETS_SENT.Name: UI_SENTTRAIL_NAME
JETS_SENT.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB
JETS_SENT.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

The jetpack exhaust is fitted with a high-concentrate pugneum dispenser. When the jets are activated, the resulting reaction carves miniature distortions in reality, and creates an interesting visual effect.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

EXPD_POSTER05A.Name: BLD_EXPD_POSTER5A_NAME
EXPD_POSTER05A.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
EXPD_POSTER05A.Description_Text:

EXPD_POSTER05B.Name: BLD_EXPD_POSTER5B_NAME
EXPD_POSTER05B.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
EXPD_POSTER05B.Description_Text:

EXPD_PETCUST05.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_PET_CUSTOM_SUB
EXPD_PETCUST05.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Companion Appearance Enhancement<>. Ideal for fierce-tempered companions, this stylish plate armour protects vital organs against laser and projectile fire. Ultra-soft breathable padding reduces the likelihood of companions wriggling out of the accessory.

Earn the trust of wild animals to adopt companions. Interact with companions to customise their appearance.

EXPD_BACKPACK05.Name: UI_EXPD_BACKPACK_05_NAME
EXPD_BACKPACK05.Subtitle: UI_BACKPACK2_SUB

An elegant wing-assisted jetpack, inspired by the design philosophy of exotic starships. This exclusive exosuit augmentation commemorates completion of the 'Exobiology' <STELLAR>Expedition<>.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

SHIP_PIRATE.Subtitle: UI_SHIPTRAIL_SUB

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

BLD_MINI_BIOFRI.Subtitle: BLD_MINI_BIOFRIG_SUB
BLD_MINI_BIOFRI.Description_Text:
A juvenile cosmic leviathan, suitable for rehoming in a habitable base.

This mysterious creature is enclosed in a chrono-preservation field to ensure it remains eternally young, playful, and a manageable size.

This peaceful space giant is a mutation of organism and starcraft, and can be tamed to swim through the stars alongside a fleet of frigates.

Recruiting this creature will add it to your frigate fleet. Manage your fleet from a <TECHNOLOGY>Fleet Command Room<> aboard your freighter, and consult your <TECHNOLOGY>Navigator<> to deploy frigates on lucrative expeditions.

FREI_TRAIL_GRAV.Subtitle: UI_FREI_TRAIL_SUB
FREI_TRAIL_GRAV.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Freighter Engine Flare Modifier<>.

High-energy exhaust gases rapid condense as they exit the freighter's colossal engines, collapsing into micro-singularities.

Transform the appearance of your freighter at the <TECHNOLOGY>Upgrade Control Terminal<> on the <VAL_ON>bridge<>.

EXPD_CAPE08.Name: UI_FLEETCAPE_NAME
EXPD_CAPE08.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_CAPE_SUB
EXPD_CAPE08.Description_Text:

Master, commander, voyager of the stars. Don your cloak and prepare to take the helm.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

BLD_MAPTUBE.Name: BLD_MAPTUBE_NAME
BLD_MAPTUBE.Subtitle: BLD_MAPTUBE_SUB
BLD_MAPTUBE.Description_Text:
A secure containment vessel, designed to provide a near-indestructible chamber for the storage of vital navigation charts.

Resilient and designed to last thousands of years, this archive is entirely free of electronic components.

BLD_FIREPIT.Name: BLD_FIREPIT_NAME
BLD_FIREPIT.Subtitle: BLD_FIREPIT_SUB
BLD_FIREPIT.Description_Text:
A low-tech heating device, ideal for generating light and heat without access to high-energy power sources.

User is advised to keep arms and legs outside of the barrel at all times.

BLD_DATASIGN.Name: BLD_DATASIGN_NAME
BLD_DATASIGN.Subtitle: BLD_DATASIGN_SUB
BLD_DATASIGN.Description_Text:
A arrangement of dynamic glass panels, each filled with undoubtedly useful and valuable information.

This display unit also functions as a source of illumination.

Floating within the shell is a haunting glow, a beacon both beautiful and cursed.

Scans indicate the being within has the genetic potential to be <SPECIAL>gelatinous<> and <TECHNOLOGY>spectral<>.

This versatile craft is plated with radiation-resistant armour, and engineered with an aerodynamic profile for agility during atmospheric flight. Claim<> this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

A harmonic generation device converts the output of the freighter engines to <FUEL>A T L A S<> frequencies, radiating a painfully crimson trail.

JETS_CORRUPT.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB
JETS_CORRUPT.Description_Text:

The jetpack exhaust is augmented with an atlantideum filter. When activated, its discordant effect is spilled across the landscape, a trail of dissonant reverberations that echo on an unknowable frequency.

Humidifiers discharge a highly salinated mist from the rocket nozzles, conducting a dramatic streak of electricity during Jetpack operation.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

EXPD_EGG_11.Name: UI_EXPD_EGG_11_NAME
EXPD_EGG_11.Subtitle: UI_EXPD_EGG_11_SUB
EXPD_EGG_11.Description_Text:
A metal 'egg' capsule, <TRADEABLE>ready to deploy!<>

A low hum resonates from deep within the capsule, its dissonant frequency turning the air around it a faint purple.

Scans indicate the being within is programmed to be <SPECIAL>free-spirited<> and <SPECIAL>defiant<>.

EXPD_PETCUST11.Name: UI_EXPD_PET_CUSTOM_11_NAME
EXPD_PETCUST11.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_PET_CUSTOM_SUB
EXPD_PETCUST11.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Companion Appearance Enhancement<>. This biomechanical remnant is a constant reminder of the many and diverse forms that existence can take.

Earn the trust of wild animals to adopt companions. Interact with companions to customise their appearance.

BLD_BUI_HAND.Name: BLD_BUI_HAND_NAME
BLD_BUI_HAND.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
BLD_BUI_HAND.Description_Text:
An exclusive buildable base ornament.

A partially assembled robotic hand, as seen on mechanical lifeforms across the galaxy. The unit is severly damaged and appears to contain no trace of Autophage entity inhabitation...

BLD_BUI_HEAD.Name: BLD_BUI_HEAD_NAME
BLD_BUI_HEAD.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
BLD_BUI_HEAD.Description_Text:
An exclusive buildable base ornament.

This is a detailed replica of an Autophage facial cage. The unit is inoperable and contains no trace of Autophage entity inhabitation...

BLD_BUI_TENT.Name: BLD_BUI_TENT_NAME
BLD_BUI_TENT.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE

S10_PART1A.Name: UI_SPEC_CONSTRUCT_HEAD_A_NAME
S10_PART1A.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_HEAD_SUB
S10_PART1A.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

The circuit cage and primary control sensors for a <TECHNOLOGY>primitive automaton<>. Plans for a unit of this design were extracted from an <STELLAR>autophage<> left at an abandoned junker's camp, before being infused with <SPECIAL>Atlantideum<>.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

TWITCH_GUN24.Description_Text: An exclusive Multi-Tool<>. This A-class weapon comes equipped with a range of pre-installed technologies and upgrades. Take<> this Multi-Tool to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current Multi-Tool. Swap between active Multi-Tools from the Utilities section of the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

TWITCH_GUNUP01A.Name: UI_TWIT_GUN_UP_01_NAME
TWITCH_GUNUP01A.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_GUN_UP_SUB
TWITCH_GUNUP01A.Description_Text:
A bundle of upgrades compatible with all <STELLAR>person Multi-Tools<>.

Includes a <TECHNOLOGY>Multi-Tool Expansion Slot<>, which may be wired into a Multi-Tool at a Space Station <STELLAR>Multi-Tool Upgrade Rack<>, as well as a unique <TECHNOLOGY>Upgrade Module<>, which can be immediately installed by hand to enhance an existing Multi-Tool technology.

An aggressive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>, modeled on the war helmets of the ancient Gek.
Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

SPEC_VYK_ARMOUR.Name: SPEC_VYKEEN_ARMOUR_NAME
SPEC_VYK_ARMOUR.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_ARMOUR_SUB
SPEC_VYK_ARMOUR.Description_Text: Powerful shoulder armour, this Exosuit augmentation comes with high-voltage connections into the user's skeletal system. This current jolts the user's body as required, manipulating the muscles into their optimal defensive posture.

SPEC_VYK_TORSO.Name: SPEC_VYKEEN_TORSO_NAME
SPEC_VYK_TORSO.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_TORSO_SUB
SPEC_VYK_TORSO.Description_Text: Reinforced yet stylish, this Exosuit chest armour provides excellent abdominal protection without compromising on looks.

SPEC_VYK_GLOVES.Name: SPEC_VYKEEN_GLOVES_NAME
SPEC_VYK_GLOVES.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_GLOVE_SUB
SPEC_VYK_GLOVES.Description_Text: Armoured gloves, perfect for wielding weapons, impressing martial cultures, and picking really spiky plants.

SPEC_VYK_LEGS.Name: SPEC_VYKEEN_LEGS_NAME
SPEC_VYK_LEGS.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_LEGS_SUB
SPEC_VYK_LEGS.Description_Text:
Carefully woven nano-fibres make these leggings both flexible and resistant to small-arms fire.

Washing requires specialist equipment.

SPEC_VYK_BOOTS.Name: SPEC_VYKEEN_BOOTS_NAME
SPEC_VYK_BOOTS.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_BOOTS_SUB
SPEC_VYK_BOOTS.Description_Text:
Reinforced foot protection system with integrated tread-balancing gyroscopes.

Hundreds of years of high-tech research, as applied to footwear.

SPEC_EXOTIC1.Name: UI_SPEC_EXOTICHEAD_01_NAME
SPEC_EXOTIC1.Subtitle: UI_EXOTIC_HEAD_SUB
SPEC_EXOTIC1.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

This part silicone, part biological helmet can detect and replicate the facial muscle movements of the wearer, creating the appearance of a natural head. It is fully compatible with exosuit technology and provides all protection of a traditional helmet.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

SPEC_SPOOKYHEAD.Subtitle: UI_EXOTIC_HEAD_SUB
SPEC_SPOOKYHEAD.Description_Text:
Naturally transform your appearance via the application of a flesh-hungry parasite. This living being partially fuses with the brainstem of its host, sealing their symbiosis.

Cautiously transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

NEW_BACKPACK.Name: UI_BACKPACK2_NAME
NEW_BACKPACK.Subtitle: UI_BACKPACK2_SUB
NEW_BACKPACK.Description_Text:

A tough, modular backpack unit. Its styling calls to mind a previous era of exploration.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Precisely calibrated multi-chromatic injectors alter the Jetpack's output, turning the exhaust trail into a vibrant display of colour.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

JETS_DARK.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB

Precisely calibrated multi-chromatic injectors alter the Pulse Engine's output, turning the exhaust trail into a vibrant display of colour.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

BASE_ROBOTOY.Name: BLD_ROBOTTOY_NAME
BASE_ROBOTOY.Subtitle: BLD_ROBOTTOY_SUB
BASE_ROBOTOY.Description_Text:
A perfectly-programmed and error free drone.

This miniature robot will be a lively presence in your base, bringing joy, laughter and a constant low-level humming to your home.

BASE_TOYCUBE.Name: BLD_TOYCUBE_NAME
BASE_TOYCUBE.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_STATUE_SUB
BASE_TOYCUBE.Description_Text:
An exclusive decorative curiosity.

This precisely crafted gadget utilises a localised gravitational field, delighting and fascinating base visitors.

BASE_TOYSPHERE.Name: BLD_TOYSPHERE_NAME
BASE_TOYSPHERE.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_STATUE_SUB
BASE_TOYSPHERE.Description_Text:
An exclusive decorative curiosity for bases.

This gadget emits a spherical hologram, representative of one of the quintillions of celestial bodies populating the galaxies.

BASE_TOYJELLY.Name: BLD_TOYJELLY_NAME
BASE_TOYJELLY.Subtitle: BLD_TOYJELLY_DESC
BASE_TOYJELLY.Description_Text:
The captured essence of an abyssal horror, contained for scientific and decorative use.

The bounding forcefield is of the very highest quality. The companion cannot escape. The companion will not escape. Escape.

BASE_TREE01.Name: BLD_TREE_1_NAME
BASE_TREE01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TREE01.Description_Text:
A large decorative fruit tree.

Fruit form, toxicity and existence will vary according to local climatic and pollinator conditions.

BASE_TREE02.Name: BLD_TREE_2_NAME
BASE_TREE02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TREE02.Description_Text:
A thin, non-fruiting tree. Root system is integrated with highly-adapted fungal symbiotes.

Supplied with its own mushrooms for ease of establishment. Fungus is non-toxic and non-spreading.

BASE_TREE03.Name: BLD_TREE_3_NAME
BASE_TREE03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TREE03.Description_Text:
A hardy evergreen tree, able to survive in a wide-range of climates.

Waxy leaves with a silvery underside provide excellent light harvesting abilities, as well as year-round interest and colour.

BASE_MEDPLANT01.Name: BLD_MEDPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_MEDPLANT01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_MEDPLANT01.Description_Text:
A medium-sized decorative plant. Each of its leaves is covered in a thin film of sticky latex. Insects that land on these leaves are slowly absorbed by digestive hormones mixed in with the glue.

Avoid accidental skin contact.

BASE_MEDPLANT02.Name: BLD_MEDPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_MEDPLANT02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_MEDPLANT02.Description_Text:
A squat, easily-managed form of the larger palm species.

Place outdoors to attract wildlife and to purify the air.

BASE_MEDPLANT03.Name: BLD_MEDPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_MEDPLANT03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_MEDPLANT03.Description_Text:
Sprouting decorative corn. Comes in a variety of colours. May attract decorative wildlife.

Unable to reproduce naturally. Must be hand-pollinated.

BASE_AQUARIUM.Name: BLD_AQUARIUM_NAME
BASE_AQUARIUM.Subtitle: BLD_AQUARIUM_SUBTITLE
BASE_AQUARIUM.Description_Text:
A small observatory unit for studying aquatic behaviours.

Completely self-contained, with its own renewable energy source, pump array, and self-cleaning filtration systems.

BASE_WPLANT1.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_WPLANT1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT1.Description_Text: A delicate marine invertebrate, cultivated for potted growth. Its distinctive looping structure gives it an attractive whimsical appearance.

BASE_WPLANT2.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_WPLANT2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT2.Description_Text: An eye-catching cluster of crystallised oceanic minerals. These crystals grow in a shard-like structure, and feature an unusual marbled colouration.

BASE_WPLANT3.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_WPLANT3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT3.Description_Text: A striking plant featuring luminescent, orb-shaped flowers. This domestic variety has adapted to absorb and process oxygen from any source, whether growing on land or underwater.

BASE_WPLANT4.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_4_NAME
BASE_WPLANT4.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT4.Description_Text: A carnivorous marine organism. An armoured shell encloses the core polyp, exposing only the stinging tentacles. Involuntary nerve spasms cause the creature to writhe perpetually: always seeking, always hungering.

BASE_WPLANT5.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_5_NAME
BASE_WPLANT5.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT5.Description_Text: A giant calcium formation, naturally configured into a strip of non-orientable space. Adds a mysterious deep-sea quality to any habitable base.

BASE_WPLANT6.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_6_NAME
BASE_WPLANT6.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT6.Description_Text: A rock formation pulled from the floor of a densely-populated ocean. The attached marine life is lacquered in a nutrient-rich mucus, to keep it fed and moist in terrestrial conditions.

BASE_BARNACLE.Name: BLD_BARNACLE_NAME
BASE_BARNACLE.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_BARNACLE.Description_Text:
A tenacious arthropod, naturally found encrusting stationary or slow-moving underwater objects.

This variety can be encouraged to affix itself to a chosen position, adding an aged marine appearance to bases.

SPEC_FIREWORK01.Name: FIREWORK_PROD_BLUE_NAME
SPEC_FIREWORK01.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB
SPEC_FIREWORK01.Description_Text: A luxury firework, rich in magnesium and indium. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

SPEC_FIREWORK02.Name: FIREWORK_PROD_RED_NAME
SPEC_FIREWORK02.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB
SPEC_FIREWORK02.Description_Text: A luxury firework, rich in magnesium and cadmium. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

SPEC_FIREWORK03.Name: FIREWORK_PROD_GREEN_NAME
SPEC_FIREWORK03.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB
SPEC_FIREWORK03.Description_Text: A luxury firework, rich in magnesium and emeril. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

SPEC_FIREWORK04.Name: UI_FIREWORK_PROD_TRIPLE_NAME
SPEC_FIREWORK04.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB
SPEC_FIREWORK04.Description_Text: A luxury firework, featuring a triple-burst symphony of colour. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

SPEC_FIREWORK05.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB
SPEC_FIREWORK05.Description_Text: A luxury firework, exploding into sparkling wedges of indium and cadmium. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

SPEC_FIREWORK06.Name: UI_FIREWORK_PROD_WHEEL_NAME
SPEC_FIREWORK06.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB
SPEC_FIREWORK06.Description_Text: A luxury firework. When activated, this pyrotechnic marvel turns and whorls in a mesmerising spiral. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

SPEC_FIREWORK07.Name: UI_FIREWORK_PROD_TITAN_R_NAME
SPEC_FIREWORK07.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB
SPEC_FIREWORK07.Description_Text: This exotic firework, tinted with cadmium<> salts, is inspired by the undulating form of the titanic sandworm. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

SPEC_FIREWORK09.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB

SPEC_FIREWORK10.Name: UI_FIREWORK_PROD_SWIRL_P_NAME
SPEC_FIREWORK10.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB

SPEC_FIREWORK11.Subtitle: BLD_FIREWORK_LAUNCHER_SUB

BASE_TOYCORE.Name: BLD_TOYCORE_NAME
BASE_TOYCORE.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_STATUE_SUB
BASE_TOYCORE.Description_Text:
An exclusive decorative curiosity for bases.

A model of reality itself, as viewed from the perspective of an impossible observer. Infinite levels of detail wait to be discovered by the viewer with a powerful enough lens.

BASE_TERRARIUM.Name: BLD_TERRARIUM_NAME
BASE_TERRARIUM.Subtitle: BLD_TERRARIUM_SUBTITLE
BASE_TERRARIUM.Description_Text:
A small observatory unit for studying animal behaviours.

Completely self-contained, complete with inbuilt nutrient processor, air purifier and faecal disposal system.

BASE_HOTPLANT01.Name: BLD_HOTPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_HOTPLANT01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOTPLANT01.Description_Text:
A large-leafed, heat resistant tree.

Its broad fronds are laced with minerals, forming a protective barrier against the harsh sunlight of its native conditions.

BASE_HOTPLANT02.Name: BLD_HOTPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_HOTPLANT02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOTPLANT02.Description_Text:
A thin tree with a large, fleshy root system, well adapted to hot climates.

Root bulb may be tapped for a source of drinkable liquid, but this is not advised outside of the most dire circumstances.

BASE_HOTPLANT03.Name: BLD_HOTPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_HOTPLANT03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOTPLANT03.Description_Text: A garden module, complete with decorative mineral formation and built-in capillary matting for optimum humidity control.

BASE_RADPLANT01.Name: BLD_RADPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_RADPLANT01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_RADPLANT01.Description_Text:
A native of radioactive worlds, this curiously meaty succulent seems to sway gently even when the air is still...

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_RADPLANT02.Name: BLD_RADPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_RADPLANT02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_RADPLANT02.Description_Text:
This decorative tree has evolved to cope with high levels of background radiation. Its central glowing core attracts wildlife and is in no way a sense organ. It does not watch you.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_RADPLANT03.Name: BLD_RADPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_RADPLANT03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_RADPLANT03.Description_Text:
This beautiful statement tree thrives in the heat of intense gamma radiation. To ensure survival in non-native environments, a chunk of high-energy material has been embedded in the trunk.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_TOXPLANT01.Name: BLD_TOXPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_TOXPLANT01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TOXPLANT01.Description_Text:
This swollen protuberance grows rapidly from a fine network of underground spores. Greatly improves nearby soil quality.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_TOXPLANT02.Name: BLD_TOXPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_TOXPLANT02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TOXPLANT02.Description_Text:
While this plant can be cultivated as a crop, consumption is not advised.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_TOXPLANT03.Name: BLD_TOXPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_TOXPLANT03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TOXPLANT03.Description_Text:
This delightful architectural floral combines two highly popular aesthetics: wriggling tentacles and giant fungi.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_DUSTPLANT1.Name: BLD_DUSTPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_DUSTPLANT1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_DUSTPLANT1.Description_Text:
Elegant feathery filaments run around this desert plant, increasing the surface area for moisture absorption. They also look very fetching.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_DUSTPLANT2.Name: BLD_DUSTPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_DUSTPLANT2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_DUSTPLANT2.Description_Text:
Delightful succulent baubles, these lovely plants top their bulbous bodies with a show of beautiful flowers.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_DUSTPLANT3.Name: BLD_DUSTPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_DUSTPLANT3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_DUSTPLANT3.Description_Text:
The bark on this tree is misleading. Neither rough nor hard, its flesh is instead soft and moist to the touch. Wrinkles in the surface store extra water for times of hardship.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_COLDPLANT1.Name: BLD_COLDPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_COLDPLANT1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_COLDPLANT1.Description_Text:
This tough conifer pumps its sap with anti-freezing enzymes, allowing it to survive unimaginably low temperatures.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_COLDPLANT2.Name: BLD_COLDPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_COLDPLANT2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_COLDPLANT2.Description_Text:
A snow-filled stone trough. This is the perfect home for the small, tough plants that grow on ice-bound worlds.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_COLDPLANT3.Name: BLD_COLDPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_COLDPLANT3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_COLDPLANT3.Description_Text:
This tree lives on an almost geological time scale. Low heat and light levels in their native habitat restrict growth to mere millimeters each season. A sample this size is a botanical marvel.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_ROCK01.Name: BLD_ROCK_1_NAME
BASE_ROCK01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_ROCK01.Description_Text:
A pleasing mineral formation, crystalised from oceanic salts. May also contain aquatic fossils and/or lifeforms.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_ROCK02.Name: BLD_ROCK_2_NAME
BASE_ROCK02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_ROCK02.Description_Text:
A remarkable piece of geological geometry. A stable load-bearing arch, infused with curiously angular solid geodes.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_ROCK03.Name: BLD_ROCK_3_NAME
BASE_ROCK03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_ROCK03.Description_Text:
Once a discarded byproduct of deep-level crystal mining, the aesthetic value of the rocks is now better appreciated.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_SWAMP1.Name: BLD_SWAMPPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_SWAMP1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_SWAMP1.Description_Text:
This species of fungus is notable for its dense capillary network and bioluminescent qualities. A circulating chain of chemical reactions produces the toadstool's nocturnal glow.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_SWAMP2.Name: BLD_SWAMPPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_SWAMP2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_SWAMP2.Description_Text:
This ancient stump was harvested from a clonal tree colony, estimated to have lived for over a hundred millennia. Its bark releases a pleasant mossy fragrance.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_SWAMP3.Name: BLD_SWAMPPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_SWAMP3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_SWAMP3.Description_Text:
This simple mud hut was modelled after a mysterious structure discovered in the mists of planet Saxm A13. Similar structures have been found throughout the universe, with no proven hypothesis regarding their origin.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_HOUDINI1.Name: BLD_HOUDINIPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_HOUDINI1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOUDINI1.Description_Text:
A proteinous formation of unknown origin, replicated aboard the Space Anomaly. Its skeletal structure often retains pockets of air, leading to slightly warmer or cooler temperatures in the centre of the cage.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_HOUDINI2.Name: BLD_HOUDINIPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_HOUDINI2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOUDINI2.Description_Text:
This unusual lifeform, dominated by a wheel of photophore glands, is difficult to classify neatly into flora or fauna. The thick columns of thorns help protect the flavoursome glands from predators.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_HOUDINI3.Name: BLD_HOUDINIPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_HOUDINI3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOUDINI3.Description_Text:
The eye-like protrusions on this bizarre organism are capable of both processing light and performing simple calculations, although it is unclear what they are watching for...

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_INFEST1.Name: BLD_INFESTEDPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_INFEST1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_INFEST1.Description_Text:
This eggshell still whispers a faint song, as though connected to a distant chorus...

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_INFEST2.Name: BLD_INFESTEDPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_INFEST2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_INFEST2.Description_Text:
The broad, plate-like leaf topping this tree is highly efficient for photosynthesis, and wild specimens can grow to extraordinary heights. This domestic variety is cultivated to be suitable to furnish habitations.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_INFEST3.Name: BLD_INFESTEDPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_INFEST3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_INFEST3.Description_Text:
This vegetative structure is high in antioxidants, though a thick layer of scales makes it impractical for farming.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_LAVA1.Name: BLD_LAVAPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_LAVA1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_LAVA1.Description_Text:
A quiet roar sounds from within this natural crystal formation, lava and gas dancing in a perpetual cycle of heating and solidifying. Mesmerising to the eye, but despite the ultrahot core, only slightly warm to the touch.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_LAVA2.Name: BLD_LAVAPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_LAVA2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_LAVA2.Description_Text:
This hybrid of egg and rock is known to form around the larvae of certain species, keeping the vulnerable creature warm and protected as it develops over the course of several decades. Membranous splits in the rock's surface expose the ever-shifting molten heart.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_LAVA3.Name: BLD_LAVAPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_LAVA3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_LAVA3.Description_Text:
Although primitive in design, this habitation heater is nonetheless a popular home furnishing. Its hypnotic flames and gentle crackling lend a comforting ambience to any room.

Provides interior decoration opportunities for bases.

BASE_CAVE1.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_CAVE1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE1.Description_Text: This fungal growth, identifiable by its wide, smooth cap and luminescent pores, is native to a variety of cave biomes. Saucer Fungi enjoy a symbiotic relationship with many species of burrowing creatures.

BASE_CAVE2.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_CAVE2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE2.Description_Text: A hardy variety of lampenflora. This creeping vine occurs naturally in damp, subterranean environments, but will thrive as a free-standing shrub in any biome type.

BASE_CAVE3.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_CAVE3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE3.Description_Text: This attractive glowing flower is remarkable for its scent, reminiscent of freshly tilled soil. Due to the plant's mineral-rich diet, the stamens often contain traces of cobalt.

BASE_CAVE4.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_4_NAME
BASE_CAVE4.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE4.Description_Text: Clusters of these large mushrooms can be found growing in underground caves. The surface 'veins' form part of an unusual gill structure, releasing spores from both above and below the fungus's cap.

BASE_CAVE5.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_5_NAME
BASE_CAVE5.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE5.Description_Text: This stalagmite was formed by the dripping of cobalt-rich moisture over several millennia. It is eternally cold to the touch, as though the rock recalls the temperature of its home cave.

BASE_NEXUS1.Name: BLD_NEXUSPROP_1_NAME
BASE_NEXUS1.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_NEXUS_PROP_SUB
BASE_NEXUS1.Description_Text: This spiked chamber contains a globule of antimatter, creating an unusual display piece for discerning base builders.

BASE_NEXUS2.Name: BLD_NEXUSPROP_2_NAME
BASE_NEXUS2.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_NEXUS_PROP_SUB
BASE_NEXUS2.Description_Text:
A replica of the mysterious orb utilised by Polo's Quicksilver Synthesis Companion.

The physical properties of the orb are forever shifting in strangely rhythmic patterns: temperature, radioactivity and density all fluctuating to an unheard song.

BASE_NEXUS3.Name: BLD_NEXUSPROP_3_NAME
BASE_NEXUS3.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_NEXUS_PROP_SUB
BASE_NEXUS3.Description_Text: A miniaturised replica of the bubbling 'liquid' vat which forms part of the Space Anomaly's anatomy. This mesmerising ornament brings an echo of Polo and Nada's anomalous home to planetary bases.

BASE_BUBPIPE.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_MAGIC_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'.

Intelligently welds into <SPECIAL>different shapes<> to create mesmerising displays in your base.

BASE_BUBPIPE_S.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE_S.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE_S.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

BASE_BUBPIPE_L.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_L_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE_L.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE_L.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This L-shaped configuration allows for curves in duct connections.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

BASE_BUBPIPE_T.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_T_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE_T.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE_T.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This T-shaped configuration allows for creating branches in duct connections.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

BASE_BUBPIPE_X.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_X_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE_X.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE_X.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This X-shaped configuration allows for connecting four ducts in a cruciform arrangement.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

S_SAIL0.Name: BLD_S_SAIL0_NAME
S_SAIL0.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
S_SAIL0.Description_Text: This full sail replicates the design of the ancient maritime trade vessels of the Gek, and makes for a striking nautical-themed home decoration.

S_SAIL1.Name: BLD_S_SAIL1_NAME
S_SAIL1.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
S_SAIL1.Description_Text: These offset sails replicate the design of the ancient maritime trade vessels of the Gek, and make for a striking nautical-themed home decoration.

S_SAIL2.Name: BLD_S_SAIL2_NAME
S_SAIL2.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
S_SAIL2.Description_Text: These asymmetrical sails replicate the design of the ancient maritime trade vessels of the Gek, and make for a striking nautical-themed home decoration.

S_SAIL3.Name: BLD_S_SAIL3_NAME
S_SAIL3.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
S_SAIL3.Description_Text: This draped canvas half-sail replicates the design of the ancient maritime trade vessels of the Gek, and makes for a striking nautical-themed home decoration.

BUILDCHAIR4.Name: BLD_BUILDCHAIR4_NAME
BUILDCHAIR4.Subtitle: BLD_CHAIR_SUBTITLE
BUILDCHAIR4.Description_Text: A sturdy, well-constructed seat, standardised for installation in Space Stations across the galaxies. Its angular design is surprisingly ergonomic.

PLANTPOT4.Name: BLD_PLANTPOT4_NAME
PLANTPOT4.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
PLANTPOT4.Description_Text: This clay plant pot features a climate neutralising field, nutrient recycling system, and integrated drip tray. Ideal for showcasing decorative plants or other decorations.

BASE_GRASS1.Name: BLD_GRASS_1_NAME
BASE_GRASS1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS1.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. This variety is characterised by very long, thin blades, covered in very fine hairs.

BASE_GRASS2.Name: BLD_GRASS_2_NAME
BASE_GRASS2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS2.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. This variety, like its taller cousin, is characterised by long hirsute blades - but grows more densely, with slightly heftier blades.

BASE_GRASS3.Name: BLD_GRASS_3_NAME
BASE_GRASS3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS3.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. The wide, flat blades secrete a fragrant, unpleasant-tasting sap to deter predators.

BASE_GRASS4.Name: BLD_GRASS_4_NAME
BASE_GRASS4.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS4.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. This variety features attractively curled blades, which furl and unfurl to allow the plant to maintain a constant internal temperature.

BASE_GRASS5.Name: BLD_GRASS_5_NAME
BASE_GRASS5.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS5.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. Closely related to certain varieties of seaweed, ribbon grass can be identified by its long rippling blades and fine hexagonal surface texture.

BASE_GRASS6.Name: BLD_GRASS_6_NAME
BASE_GRASS6.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS6.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. Cloven paw bears more structural similarity to a shrub than a true grass, and features large glossy leaves for rapid photosynthesis.

BASE_GRASS7.Name: BLD_GRASS_7_NAME
BASE_GRASS7.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS7.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. The branching blades of this variety are formed of woody, twig-like armour insulating thick veins of moisture-storing resin.

BASE_FLOWER1.Name: BLD_FLOWER_1_NAME
BASE_FLOWER1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_FLOWER1.Description_Text: A hardy floral patch, genetically modified to thrive in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. Barbed petals protect the flowers from would-be predators, piercing flesh with a deadly toxin. Haz-Mat Gauntlets recommended while handling.

BASE_FLOWER2.Name: BLD_FLOWER_2_NAME
BASE_FLOWER2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_FLOWER2.Description_Text: A hardy floral patch, genetically modified to thrive in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. These unusually-shaped flowers are packed with pollen, and release a dizzyingly sweet perfume.

BASE_FLOWER3.Name: BLD_FLOWER_3_NAME
BASE_FLOWER3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_FLOWER3.Description_Text: A hardy floral patch, genetically modified to thrive in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. These ligulate blossoms remain open day and night, absorbing light from both local and distant stars.

BLD_COVSILOS.Name: BLD_COVEREDSILOS_NAME
BLD_COVSILOS.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
BLD_COVSILOS.Description_Text: A set of tarpaulin-draped silo barrels, containing cargo of questionable provenance.

BLD_COVCRATE.Name: BLD_COVEREDCRATE_NAME
BLD_COVCRATE.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
BLD_COVCRATE.Description_Text: A large crate, sealed and prepared for transportation. The tarpaulin wrapping conceals the precise nature of this cargo, obscuring whether all the export stamps are where they ought to be...

BLD_CRANE.Name: BLD_CRANE_NAME
BLD_CRANE.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
BLD_CRANE.Description_Text: Heavy machinery, for lifting and relocating heavy cargo. Despite the crane's size, the rotation-resistant hoist rope and AI-corrected swivel allow for extremely precise movements.

S_SIGN_BAR1.Name: BLD_S_SIGN_BAR1_NAME
S_SIGN_BAR1.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
S_SIGN_BAR1.Description_Text:
An attention-grabbing welcome sign, illuminated by an array of gas-discharge tubes.

Design salvaged from the "Euclid Moonrise", a Vy'keen joint with an insalubrious reputation.

S_SIGN_BAR2.Name: BLD_S_SIGN_BAR2_NAME
S_SIGN_BAR2.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
S_SIGN_BAR2.Description_Text:
An attention-grabbing welcome sign, illuminated by an array of gas-discharge tubes.

Design salvaged from the lively Gek saloon known as the "Ship and Pilot".

S_SIGN_BAR3.Name: BLD_S_SIGN_BAR3_NAME
S_SIGN_BAR3.Name_Text: "THE BLACK HOLE IN THE WALL" SIGN
S_SIGN_BAR3.NameLower_Text: "The Black Hole in the Wall" Sign
S_SIGN_BAR3.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE
S_SIGN_BAR3.Description_Text:
An attention-grabbing welcome sign, illuminated by an array of gas-discharge tubes.

Design salvaged from an underground Korvax cantina named "The Black Hole in the Wall".

BANNER_NMSCORD.Description_Text:

BANNER_UN42.Name: UI_BANNER_UN42_NAME
BANNER_UN42.Subtitle: UI_BANNER_SUB
BANNER_UN42.Description_Text:
Equip this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<> in support of the values of community, longevity, viability, and support.

BANNER_AF.Name: UI_BANNER_AF_NAME
BANNER_AF.Subtitle: UI_BANNER_SUB
BANNER_AF.Description_Text:
Equip this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<> to represent the enigmatic organisation known as the Atlas Foundation.

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

ODD_EGG.Name: UI_ODD_EGG_NAME
ODD_EGG.Subtitle: UI_ODD_EGG_SUB
ODD_EGG.Description_Text:
An anomalous egg. The shell is tough and leathery, and twitches when touched.

A faint tapping can be heard coming from within. From time to time, it appears to sing.

MYSTERY_BEACON.Name: UI_MYSTERY_BEACON_NAME
MYSTERY_BEACON.Subtitle: UI_MYSTERY_BEACON_SUB
MYSTERY_BEACON.Description_Text:
The result of Nada's research into unusual patterns detected in the stories of the <TRANS_TRA>Gek<>, <TRANS_EXP>Korvax<>, and <TRANS_WAR>Vy'keen<>.

The beacon broadcasts a <STELLAR>signal echo<> attuned to the shift <SPECIAL>historiographical flux<> mapped by Nada's Traveller companions.

Specialist Polo is unwilling to predict the results of the broadcast.

SLIME_MED.Subtitle: BLD_SLIME_MED_SUB
SLIME_MED.Description_Text:

Though there is no evidence to suggest it would be unsafe to do so, avoid treading on the slime where possible.

SPOOKY_PLANT.Name: BLD_SPOOKY_PLANT_NAME
SPOOKY_PLANT.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
SPOOKY_PLANT.Description_Text:
The flesh of this sinister squash is always warm, and slightly luminous. Despite these strange qualities, it is quite edible, and releases a comforting aroma wherever it grows.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

SPEC_PETCUST1.Name: UI_SPEC_PET_CUSTOM_01_NAME
SPEC_PETCUST1.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_PET_CUSTOM_SUB
SPEC_PETCUST1.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Companion Appearance Enhancement<>. This articulated mining laser is insulated with a lightweight gel, ensuring ultimate comfort for companions assisting with resource harvesting.

Earn the trust of wild animals to adopt companions. Interact with companions to customise their appearance.

SPEC_PETCUST2.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_PET_CUSTOM_SUB
SPEC_PETCUST2.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Companion Appearance Enhancement<>. This compact device generates detailed analytics reports of creature traversal habits, to provide explorers with insight into the secret lives of their animal companions.

Earn the trust of wild animals to adopt companions. Interact with companions to customise their appearance.

SPEC_PETCUST3.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_PET_CUSTOM_SUB
SPEC_PETCUST3.Description_Text:

Earn the trust of wild animals to adopt companions. Interact with companions to customise their appearance.

FREI_TRAIL_GRE.Name: UI_FREI_TRAIL_GRE_NAME
FREI_TRAIL_GRE.Subtitle: UI_FREI_TRAIL_SUB
FREI_TRAIL_GRE.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Freighter Engine Flare Modifier<>.

The extreme heat of the freighter's engines excites this filter of Emeril salts, tinting the exhaust with a vivid green hue.

Transform the appearance of your freighter at the <TECHNOLOGY>Upgrade Control Terminal<> on the <VAL_ON>bridge<>.

FREI_TRAIL_YEL.Name: UI_FREI_TRAIL_YEL_NAME
FREI_TRAIL_YEL.Subtitle: UI_FREI_TRAIL_SUB
FREI_TRAIL_YEL.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Freighter Engine Flare Modifier<>.

The extreme heat of the freighter's engines excites this filter of sodium salts, tinting the exhaust with a vivid golden hue.

Transform the appearance of your freighter at the <TECHNOLOGY>Upgrade Control Terminal<> on the <VAL_ON>bridge<>.

FREI_TRAIL_PUR.Name: UI_FREI_TRAIL_PUR_NAME
FREI_TRAIL_PUR.Subtitle: UI_FREI_TRAIL_SUB
FREI_TRAIL_PUR.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Freighter Engine Flare Modifier<>.

A grid of compact particle accelerators activate with heat from the freighter engines, streaking the exhaust with a dark trail of antimatter.

Transform the appearance of your freighter at the <TECHNOLOGY>Upgrade Control Terminal<> on the <VAL_ON>bridge<>.

FREI_TRAIL_TUR.Name: UI_FREI_TRAIL_TUR_NAME
FREI_TRAIL_TUR.Subtitle: UI_FREI_TRAIL_SUB
FREI_TRAIL_TUR.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Freighter Engine Flare Modifier<>.

Organically altering the hue of freighter exhaust, this engine modification utilises the bioluminescence of abyssal sea creatures to generate its striking turquoise colouration.

Transform the appearance of your freighter at the <TECHNOLOGY>Upgrade Control Terminal<> on the <VAL_ON>bridge<>.

CAPE_JELLY.Name: UI_CAPE_JELLY_NAME
CAPE_JELLY.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_CAPE_SUB
CAPE_JELLY.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Flow across the galaxy with this cape's lattice of fluttering tentacles, woven from regenerated cellulose fibres.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

CAPE_BIOFRIG.Name: UI_CAPE_BIOFRIG_NAME
CAPE_BIOFRIG.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_CAPE_SUB
CAPE_BIOFRIG.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

In the furthest reaches of space swim <SPECIAL>cosmic megafauna<>, aligning their paths with Travellers, dreaming of possible realities.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

CAPE_WORM.Name: UI_CAPE_WORM_NAME
CAPE_WORM.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_CAPE_SUB
CAPE_WORM.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

"The worm lord towers above the dusty earth; its flesh becomes the sky."

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

CAPE_SEED.Name: UI_SEEDCAPE_NAME
CAPE_SEED.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_CAPE_SUB
CAPE_SEED.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

A vintage garment woven from a star silk blend, bearing a classic geometric design.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

HOOD_GEK.Name: UI_SPEC_HOOD_GEK_NAME
HOOD_GEK.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_HOOD_SUB
HOOD_GEK.Description_Text:
This grand hood is worn by the upper ranks of Gek at events and conventions, distinguishing the esteemed Trade Lord from the lowly Hireling.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit with this exclusive <STELLAR>Appearance Override<> at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

JETS_FIRE.Name: UI_JETTRAIL_FIRE_NAME
JETS_FIRE.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB
JETS_FIRE.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Pressurised jets breathe additional oxygen into the Jetpack flames, brightening and lengthening the exhaust trail.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

JETS_CONFETTI.Name: UI_JETTRAIL_CONFETTI_NAME
JETS_CONFETTI.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB
JETS_CONFETTI.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

A multi-coloured scattering of bio-plastic flakes adds a celebratory flair to the Jetpack's output. Expelled material is fully compostable.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

JETS_FIREWORK.Name: UI_JETTRAIL_FIREWORK_NAME
JETS_FIREWORK.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB
JETS_FIREWORK.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Pellets of chromatic metal ignite during flight, splitting into glittering stars of RGB.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

JETS_PLASMA.Name: UI_JETTRAIL_PLASMA_NAME
JETS_PLASMA.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB
JETS_PLASMA.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Replaces the standard Jetpack combustion chamber with a plasma engine. During flight, the exhaust nozzles release dazzling clouds of ionised matter.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

JETS_FUSION.Name: UI_JETTRAIL_FUSION_NAME
JETS_FUSION.Subtitle: UI_JETTRAIL_SUB
JETS_FUSION.Description_Text:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Harnesses natural stellar processes to make the Jetpack output blaze. A light-diffusing compound protects the user and onlookers from retinal damage.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

BASE_FOXGLOVE01.Name: BLD_FOXGLOVE_1_NAME
BASE_FOXGLOVE01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_FOXGLOVE01.Description_Text:

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

U_TECHBOX_CORE.Subtitle: UP_TECH_BOX_SUB

U_TECHBOX_ALIEN.Subtitle: UP_TECH_BOX_ALIEN_SUB

U_TECHPACK_CORE.Name: UP_TECH_PACK_NAME
U_TECHPACK_CORE.Subtitle: UP_TECH_PACK_SUB
